  <section class=3D"informative" id=3D"intro"><!--OddPage--><div class=3D"h=
eader-wrapper"><h2 id=3D"x1-introduction"><bdi class=3D"secno">1.<!---0.032=
930%--> </bdi>Introduction</h2><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.g=
ithub.io/mediacapture-main/#intro" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 1.">=
</a></div><p><em>This section is non-normative.<!---0.032930%--></em></p>
   =20
    <p>This document defines APIs for requesting access to local multimedia
    devices, such as microphones or video cameras.</p>
    <p>This document also defines the MediaStream API, which provides the m=
eans
    to control where multimedia stream data is consumed, and provides some
    control over the devices that produce the media. It also exposes
    information about devices able to capture and render media.</p>
  </section>
  <section id=3D"conformance"><!--OddPage--><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><=
h2 id=3D"x2-conformance"><bdi class=3D"secno">2.<!---0.032930%--> </bdi>Con=
formance<!---0.032930%--></h2><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.gi=
thub.io/mediacapture-main/#conformance" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section=
 2."></a></div><p>As well as sections marked as non-normative, all authorin=
g guidelines, diagrams, examples, and notes in this specification are non-n=
ormative. Everything else in this specification is normative.<!---0.032930%=
--></p><p>
        The key words<!---0.032930%--> <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY<!---0.0329=
30%--></em>, <!---0.032930%--><em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></=
em>, <!---0.032930%--><em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST NOT<!---0.032930%--></em>,=
 <!---0.032930%--><em class=3D"rfc2119">NOT REQUIRED<!---0.032930%--></em>,=
 and <!---0.032930%--><em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD<!---0.032930%--></em><!-=
--0.032930%--> in this document
        are<!---0.032930%--> to be interpreted as described in
        <a href=3D"https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/bcp14">BCP 14</a>
        [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https:=
//w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#bib-rfc2119" title=3D"Key words for use =
in RFCs to Indicate Requirement Levels">RFC2119<!---0.032930%--></a></cite>=
<!---0.032930%-->]<!---0.032930%--> [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-ty=
pe=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#bib-rfc8174"=
 title=3D"Ambiguity of Uppercase vs Lowercase in RFC 2119 Key Words">RFC817=
4<!---0.032930%--></a></cite><!---0.032930%-->]<!---0.032930%-->
        when, and only when, they appear<!---0.032930%--> in all
        capitals, as shown here.
      </p><!---0.032930%-->
    <p>This specification defines conformance criteria that apply to a sing=
le
    product: the <dfn data-plurals=3D"user agents" id=3D"dfn-user-agent" ta=
bindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">User Agent</dfn=
> that implements the interfaces that it
    contains.</p>
    <p>Conformance requirements phrased as algorithms or specific steps may=
 be
    implemented in any manner, so long as the end result is equivalent. (In
    particular, the algorithms defined in this specification are intended t=
o be
    easy to follow, and not intended to be performant.)</p>
    <p>Implementations that use ECMAScript [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-=
link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#bib-e=
cma-262" title=3D"ECMAScript Language Specification">ECMA-262<!---0.032930%=
--></a></cite><!---0.032930%-->] to implement the APIs
    defined in this specification must implement them in a manner consisten=
t
    with the ECMAScript Bindings defined in the Web IDL specification
    [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://w3=
c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#bib-webidl" title=3D"Web IDL Standard">WEBID=
L<!---0.032930%--></a></cite><!---0.032930%-->], as this specification uses=
 that specification and
    terminology.</p>
  </section>
  <section id=3D"terminology"><!--OddPage--><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><=
h2 id=3D"x3-terminology"><bdi class=3D"secno">3.<!---0.032930%--> </bdi>Ter=
minology</h2><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapt=
ure-main/#terminology" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 3."></a></div>
   =20
    <dl>
      <dt><dfn data-export=3D"" data-plurals=3D"sources" id=3D"dfn-source" =
tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">source</dfn><=
/dt>
      <dd>
        <p>A source is the "thing" providing the source of a media stream
        track. The source is the broadcaster of the media itself. A source =
can
        be a physical webcam, microphone, local video or audio file from th=
e
        user's hard drive, network resource, or static image. Note that thi=
s
        document describes the use of microphone and camera type sources on=
ly,
        the use of other source types is described in other documents.</p>
        <p>An application that has no prior authorization regarding sources=
 is
        only given the number of available sources, their type and any
        relationship to other devices. Additional information about sources=
 can
        become available when applications are authorized to use a source (=
see
        <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#access-control-=
model" class=3D"sec-ref"><bdi class=3D"secno">9.2.1 </bdi>Access control mo=
del</a>).</p>
        <p>Sources <strong>do not</strong> have constraints =E2=80=94 track=
s have
        constraints. When a source is connected to a track, it must produce
        media that conforms to the constraints present on that track, to th=
at
        track. Multiple tracks can be attached to the same source. <a data-=
link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-ma=
in/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-1">U=
ser Agent<!---0.032930%--></a>
        processing, such as downsampling, <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY<!---0.0=
32930%--></em> be used to ensure that all tracks
        have appropriate media.</p>
        <p>Sources have constrainable properties which have
        <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/mediacapture-main/#dfn-capabilities" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-d=
fn-capabilities-1">capabilities<!---0.032930%--></a> and <a data-link-type=
=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-s=
ettings" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-settings-1">settings<!---0=
.032930%--></a>
        exposed on tracks. While the constrainable properties are "owned" b=
y
        the source, sources <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY<!---0.032930%--></em>=
 be able to accommodate different demands at
        once. For this reason, capabilities are common to any (multiple) tr=
acks
        that happen to be using the same source, whereas settings <em class=
=3D"rfc2119">MAY<!---0.032930%--></em> differ
        per track (e.g., if two different track objects bound to the same
        source query capability and settings information, they will get bac=
k
        the same capabilities, but may get different settings that are tail=
ored
        to satisfy their individual constraints).</p>
      </dd>
      <dt><dfn data-lt=3D"settings|Setting" id=3D"dfn-settings" tabindex=3D=
"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Setting</dfn> (Source Se=
tting)</dt>
      <dd>
        <p>A setting refers to the immediate, current
        value of the source's constrainable properties. Settings are always
        read-only.</p>
        <p>A source conditions may dynamically change, such as when a camer=
a
        switches to a lower frame rate due to low light conditions. In thes=
e
        cases the tracks related to the affected source might not satisfy t=
he
        set constraints any longer. The platform <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOU=
LD<!---0.032930%--></em> try to minimize such
        excursions as far as possible, but will continue to deliver media e=
ven
        when a temporary or permanent condition exists that prevents satisf=
ying
        the constraints.</p>
        <p>Although settings are a property of the source, they are only
        exposed to the application through the tracks attached to the sourc=
e.
        This is exposed via the <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacaptu=
re-main/#dom-constrainablepattern" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"=
idl" id=3D"ref-for-dom-constrainablepattern-1"><code>ConstrainablePattern</=
code></a> interface.</p>
      </dd>
      <dt><dfn data-lt=3D"capabilities|Capability" id=3D"dfn-capabilities" =
tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Capability</d=
fn></dt>
      <dd>
        <p>For each constrainable property, there is a capability that
        describes whether it is supported by the source and if so, the rang=
e of
        supported values. As with settings, capabilities are exposed to the
        application via the <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-m=
ain/#dom-constrainablepattern" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"idl"=
 id=3D"ref-for-dom-constrainablepattern-2"><code>ConstrainablePattern</code=
></a> interface.</p>
        <p>The values of the supported capabilities must be normalized to t=
he
        ranges and enumerated types defined in this specification.</p>
        <p>A <!---0.032930%--><a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-xref-type=3D"m=
ethod" data-link-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack=
" data-lt=3D"getCapabilities()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-=
main/#dom-mediastreamtrack-getcapabilities" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref=
-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-getcapabilities-1"><code>getCapabilities<!---0.03=
2930%--></code></a><code>(<!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%-=
->)</code><!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%--> call on
        a track returns the same underlying per-source capabilities for all
        tracks connected to the source.</p>
        <p>This API is intentionally simplified. Capabilities are not capab=
le
        of describing interactions between different values. For instance, =
it
        is not possible to accurately describe the capabilities of a camera
        that can produce a high resolution video stream at a low frame rate=
 and
        lower resolutions at a higher frame rate. Capabilities describe the
        complete range of each value. Interactions between constraints are
        exposed by attempting to apply constraints.</p>
      </dd>
      <dt><dfn id=3D"dfn-constraint" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog=
" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Constraint</dfn>s</dt>
      <dd>
        <p>Constraints provide a general control surface that allows
        applications to both select an appropriate source for a track and, =
once
        selected, to influence how a source operates.</p>
        <p>Constraints limit the range of operating modes that a source can=
 use
        when providing media for a track. Without provided track constraint=
s,
        implementations are free to select a source's settings from the ful=
l
        ranges of its supported capabilities. Implementations may also adju=
st
        source settings at any time within the bounds imposed by all applie=
d
        constraints.</p>
        <p><!---0.032930%--><a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-xref-type=3D"met=
hod" data-link-for=3D"MediaDevices" data-xref-for=3D"MediaDevices" data-lt=
=3D"getUserMedia()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-me=
diadevices-getusermedia" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediadevic=
es-getusermedia-1"><code>getUserMedia<!---0.032930%--></code></a><code>(<!-=
--0.032930%--><!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%-->)</code><!---0.032930%--><!=
---0.032930%--> uses constraints
        to help select an appropriate source for a track and configure it.
        Additionally, the <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-mai=
n/#dom-constrainablepattern" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"idl" i=
d=3D"ref-for-dom-constrainablepattern-3"><code>ConstrainablePattern</code><=
/a> interface on tracks
        includes an API for dynamically changing the track's constraints at=
 any
        later time.</p>
        <p>A track will not be connected to a source using
        <!---0.032930%--><a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-xref-type=3D"method=
" data-link-for=3D"MediaDevices" data-xref-for=3D"MediaDevices" data-lt=3D"=
getUserMedia()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediad=
evices-getusermedia" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediadevices-g=
etusermedia-2"><code>getUserMedia<!---0.032930%--></code></a><code>(<!---0.=
032930%--><!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%-->)</code><!---0.032930%--><!---0=
.032930%--> if its initial constraints cannot be
        satisfied. However, the ability to meet the constraints on a track =
can
        change over time, and constraints can be changed. If circumstances
        change such that constraints cannot be met, the
        <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-constrainab=
lepattern" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"idl" id=3D"ref-for-dom-c=
onstrainablepattern-4"><code>ConstrainablePattern</code></a> interface defi=
nes an appropriate error to
        inform the application. <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacaptu=
re-main/#the-model-sources-sinks-constraints-and-settings" data-matched-tex=
t=3D"[[[#the-model-sources-sinks-constraints-and-settings]]]" class=3D"sec-=
ref"><bdi class=3D"secno">5. </bdi>The model: sources, sinks, constraints, =
and settings</a> explains how
        constraints interact in more detail.</p>
        <p>For each constrainable property, a constraint exists whose name
        corresponds with the relevant source setting name and capability
        name.</p>
        <p>A constraint falls into one of three groups, depending on its pl=
ace
        in the constraints structure. The groups are:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><dfn data-plurals=3D"required constraint" id=3D"dfn-required-=
constraints" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">=
required constraints</dfn> are all <a data-lt=3D"advanced constraints" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-advanced-constraints" clas=
s=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-advanced-constra=
ints-1">non-advanced</a> constraints that are
        <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-required" c=
lass=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-required-1">r=
equired</a>.</li>
          <li><dfn id=3D"dfn-optional-basic-constraints" tabindex=3D"0" ari=
a-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">optional basic constraints</dfn=
> are the remaining
        <a data-lt=3D"advanced constraints" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/m=
ediacapture-main/#dfn-advanced-constraints" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link=
-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-advanced-constraints-2">non-advanced</a> co=
nstraints.</li>
          <li><dfn id=3D"dfn-advanced-constraints" tabindex=3D"0" aria-hasp=
opup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">advanced constraints</dfn> are all co=
nstraints specified
        using the <code><a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/=
#dom-constraints-advanced" id=3D"ref-for-dom-constraints-advanced-1">advanc=
ed</a></code>
        keyword.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>In general, <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https:=
//w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-2">User Agents<!---0.032930%--></a> will have mo=
re flexibility to optimize the
        media streaming experience the fewer constraints are applied, so
        application authors are strongly encouraged to use <a href=3D"https=
://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-required-constraints" class=3D"inte=
rnalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-required-constraints-1">r=
equired
        constraints</a> sparingly.</p>
      </dd>
    </dl>
  </section>
  <section id=3D"stream-api"><!--OddPage--><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h=
2 id=3D"x4-mediastream-api"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.<!---0.032930%--> </bdi>=
MediaStream API</h2><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/me=
diacapture-main/#stream-api" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4."></a></=
div>
   =20
    <section id=3D"introduction"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h3 id=3D"x4=
-1-introduction"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.1<!---0.032930%--> </bdi>Introducti=
on</h3><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-ma=
in/#introduction" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.1"></a></div>
     =20
      <p>The two main components in the MediaStream API are the
      <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSt=
reamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream=
track" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-1"><code>Me=
diaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> and <a data-xre=
f-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaStream" href=3D"htt=
ps://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream" class=3D"internalDFN=
" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-1"><code>MediaStream<!---0.032930%--></code=
></a><!---0.032930%--> interfaces. The
      <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSt=
reamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream=
track" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-2"><code>Me=
diaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> object represen=
ts media of a single
      type that originates from one media source in the <a data-link-type=
=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-u=
ser-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-3">User Agent=
<!---0.032930%--></a>, e.g. video
      produced by a web camera. A <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-typ=
e=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaStream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacaptur=
e-main/#dom-mediastream" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastrea=
m-2"><code>MediaStream<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> is used=
 to
      group several <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data=
-lt=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#d=
om-mediastreamtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtra=
ck-3"><code>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> o=
bjects into one unit
      that can be recorded or rendered in a media element.</p>
      <p>Each <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D=
"MediaStream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastr=
eam" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-3"><code>MediaStre=
am<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> can contain zero or more
      <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSt=
reamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream=
track" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-4"><code>Me=
diaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> objects. All tr=
acks in a
      <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSt=
ream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream" cla=
ss=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-4"><code>MediaStream<!---0=
.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> are intended to be synchronized whe=
n
      rendered. This is not a hard requirement, since it might not be possi=
ble
      to synchronize tracks from sources that have different clocks. Differ=
ent
      <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSt=
ream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream" cla=
ss=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-5"><code>MediaStream<!---0=
.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> objects do not need to be
      synchronized.</p>
      <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generatedID">=
<div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note" aria-level=
=3D"4"><span>Note</span><!---0.032930%--></div><p class=3D"">While the inte=
nt is to synchronize tracks, it could be
      better in some circumstances to permit tracks to lose synchronization=
. In
      particular, when tracks are remotely sourced and real-time [<cite><a =
class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/me=
diacapture-main/#bib-webrtc" title=3D"WebRTC: Real-Time Communication in Br=
owsers">WEBRTC<!---0.032930%--></a></cite><!---0.032930%-->],
      it can be better to allow loss of synchronization than to accumulate
      delays or risk glitches and other artifacts. Implementations are expe=
cted
      to understand the implications of choices regarding synchronization o=
f
      playback and the effect that these have on user perception.</p></div>
      <p>A single <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-l=
t=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom=
-mediastreamtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack=
-5"><code>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> can=
 represent
      multi-channel content, such as stereo or 5.1 audio or stereoscopic vi=
deo,
      where the channels have a well defined relationship to each other.
      Information about channels might be exposed through other APIs, such =
as
      [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://=
w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#bib-webaudio" title=3D"Web Audio API 1.1">=
WEBAUDIO<!---0.032930%--></a></cite><!---0.032930%-->], but this specificat=
ion provides no direct access to
      channels.</p>
      <p>A <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"Me=
diaStream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream=
" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-6"><code>MediaStream<=
!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> object has an input and an out=
put
      that represent the combined input and output of all the object's trac=
ks.
      The output of the <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" =
data-lt=3D"MediaStream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#do=
m-mediastream" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-7"><code=
>MediaStream<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> controls how the =
object
      is rendered, e.g., what is saved if the object is recorded to a file =
or
      what is displayed if the object is used in a <code><a data-xref-type=
=3D"element" data-link-type=3D"element" data-cite=3D"html" data-cite-path=
=3D"/media.html" data-cite-frag=3D"video" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.=
org/multipage/media.html#video">video<!---0.032930%--></a></code> element.
      A single <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=
=3D"MediaStream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-media=
stream" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-8"><code>MediaS=
tream<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> object can be attached t=
o
      multiple different outputs at the same time.</p>
      <p>A new <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=
=3D"MediaStream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-media=
stream" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-9"><code>MediaS=
tream<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> object can be created fr=
om
      existing media streams or tracks using the
      <!---0.032930%--><a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-xref-type=3D"method" =
data-link-for=3D"MediaStream" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStream" data-lt=3D"Medi=
aStream()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream=
" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-10"><code>MediaStream=
<!---0.032930%--></code></a><code>(<!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%--><!---0=
.032930%-->)</code><!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%--> constructor. The cons=
tructor argument
      can either be an existing <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=
=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaStream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture=
-main/#dom-mediastream" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream=
-11"><code>MediaStream<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> object,=
 in
      which case all the tracks of the given stream are added to the new
      <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSt=
ream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream" cla=
ss=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-12"><code>MediaStream<!---=
0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> object, or an array of
      <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSt=
reamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream=
track" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-6"><code>Me=
diaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> objects. The la=
tter form makes it
      possible to compose a stream from different source streams.</p>
      <p>Both <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D=
"MediaStream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastr=
eam" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-13"><code>MediaStr=
eam<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> and
      <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSt=
reamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream=
track" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-7"><code>Me=
diaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> objects can be =
cloned. A cloned
      <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSt=
ream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream" cla=
ss=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-14"><code>MediaStream<!---=
0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> contains clones of all member trac=
ks from
      the original stream. A cloned <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-t=
ype=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/medi=
acapture-main/#dom-mediastreamtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-do=
m-mediastreamtrack-8"><code>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!-=
--0.032930%--> has a
      <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#constrainable-int=
erface">set of constraints</a> that is
      independent of the instance it is cloned from, which allows media fro=
m
      the same source to have different constraints applied for different
      <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-consumer" cla=
ss=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-consumer-1">con=
sumer</a>s. The <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=
=3D"MediaStream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-media=
stream" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-15"><code>Media=
Stream<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> object is also used in
      contexts outside <!---0.032930%--><a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-xref=
-type=3D"attribute|dict-member|const" data-link-for=3D"MediaDevices" data-x=
ref-for=3D"MediaDevices" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#d=
om-mediadevices-getusermedia" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-media=
devices-getusermedia-3"><code>getUserMedia<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---=
0.032930%-->, such as [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" =
href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#bib-webrtc" title=3D"WebRT=
C: Real-Time Communication in Browsers">WEBRTC<!---0.032930%--></a></cite><=
!---0.032930%-->].</p>
    </section>
    <section id=3D"mediastream"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h3 id=3D"x4-=
2-mediastream"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.2<!---0.032930%--> </bdi><a data-xref=
-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaStream" href=3D"http=
s://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream" class=3D"internalDFN"=
 id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-16"><code>MediaStream<!---0.032930%--></code=
></a><!---0.032930%--></h3><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.githu=
b.io/mediacapture-main/#mediastream" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.=
2"></a></div>
     =20
      <p id=3D"mediastream-constructor">The MediaStream <dfn data-idl=3D"co=
nstructor" data-dfn-for=3D"MediaStream" data-export=3D"" data-dfn-type=3D"c=
onstructor" id=3D"dom-mediastream-constructor" data-title=3D"constructor" d=
ata-lt=3D"constructor()" data-local-lt=3D"MediaStream.constructor|MediaStre=
am.constructor()|constructor" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog"><code=
>constructor</code></dfn> composes a new
      stream out of existing tracks. It takes an optional argument of type
      <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSt=
ream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream" cla=
ss=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-17"><code>MediaStream<!---=
0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> or an array of
      <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSt=
reamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream=
track" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-9"><code>Me=
diaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> objects. When t=
he constructor is invoked, the User
      Agent must run the following steps:</p>
      <ol class=3D"algorithm">
        <li>
          <p>Let <var>stream</var> be a newly constructed
          <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"Med=
iaStream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream"=
 class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-18"><code>MediaStream<=
!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> object.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Initialize <var>stream</var>.<!---0.032930%--><a data-link-typ=
e=3D"idl" data-xref-type=3D"attribute|dict-member|const" data-link-for=3D"M=
ediaStream" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/med=
iacapture-main/#dom-mediastream-id" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom=
-mediastream-id-1"><code>id<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%-->  a=
ttribute to a newly generated
          value.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>If the constructor's argument is present, run the following
          steps:</p>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>Construct a set of tracks <var>tracks</var> based on the t=
ype
              of argument:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p>A <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" d=
ata-lt=3D"MediaStream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom=
-mediastream" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-19"><code=
>MediaStream<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> object:</p>
                  <p>Let <var>tracks</var> be a set containing all the
                  <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-l=
t=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom=
-mediastreamtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack=
-10"><code>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> ob=
jects in the
                  <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-l=
t=3D"MediaStream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-medi=
astream" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-20"><code>Medi=
aStream<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> <a href=3D"https://w3c=
.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-track-set" class=3D"internalDFN" data-lin=
k-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-track-set-1">track
                  set</a>.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>A sequence of <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-ty=
pe=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media=
capture-main/#dom-mediastreamtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom=
-mediastreamtrack-11"><code>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!-=
--0.032930%-->
                  objects:</p>
                  <p>Let <var>tracks</var> be a set containing all the
                  <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-l=
t=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom=
-mediastreamtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack=
-12"><code>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> ob=
jects in the provided
                  sequence.</p>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>For each <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl=
" data-lt=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-m=
ain/#dom-mediastreamtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastr=
eamtrack-13"><code>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.03293=
0%-->,
              <var>track</var> , in <var>tracks</var>, run the following
              steps:</p>
              <ol>
                <li>
                  <p>If <var>track</var> is already in <var>stream</var>'s
                  <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c=
.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-track-set" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"re=
f-for-dfn-track-set-2">track set<!---0.032930%--></a>, skip
                  <var>track</var>.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>Otherwise, add <var>track</var> to <var>stream</var>'s
                  <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c=
.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-track-set" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"re=
f-for-dfn-track-set-3">track set<!---0.032930%--></a>.</p>
                </li>
              </ol>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Return <var>stream</var>.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
      <p>The tracks of a <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl"=
 data-lt=3D"MediaStream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#d=
om-mediastream" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-21"><co=
de>MediaStream<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> are stored in a
      <dfn class=3D"export" data-export=3D"" id=3D"dfn-track-set" tabindex=
=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">track set</dfn>. The =
track set <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> contain the
      <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSt=
reamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream=
track" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-14"><code>M=
ediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> objects that c=
orrespond to the
      tracks of the stream. The relative order of the tracks in the set is =
User
      Agent defined and the API will never put any requirements on the orde=
r.
      The proper way to find a specific <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-li=
nk-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/=
mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastreamtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-fo=
r-dom-mediastreamtrack-15"><code>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></=
a><!---0.032930%-->
      object in the set is to look it up by its <!---0.032930%--><a data-li=
nk-type=3D"idl" data-xref-type=3D"attribute|dict-member|const" data-link-fo=
r=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w=
3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastreamtrack-id" class=3D"internalD=
FN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-id-1"><code>id<!---0.032930%--></cod=
e></a><!---0.032930%-->.</p>
      <p>An object that reads data from the output of a
      <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSt=
ream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream" cla=
ss=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-22"><code>MediaStream<!---=
0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> is referred to as a
      <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSt=
ream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream" cla=
ss=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-23"><code>MediaStream<!---=
0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> <dfn data-export=3D"" data-for=3D"=
MediaStream" id=3D"dfn-consumer" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" da=
ta-dfn-type=3D"dfn">consumer</dfn>. The list of
      <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSt=
ream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream" cla=
ss=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-24"><code>MediaStream<!---=
0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> consumers currently include media
      elements (such as <code><a data-xref-type=3D"element" data-link-type=
=3D"element" data-cite=3D"html" data-cite-path=3D"/media.html" data-cite-fr=
ag=3D"video" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#vide=
o">video<!---0.032930%--></a></code> and
      <code><a data-xref-type=3D"element" data-link-type=3D"element" data-c=
ite=3D"html" data-cite-path=3D"/media.html" data-cite-frag=3D"audio" href=
=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#audio">audio<!---0.03=
2930%--></a></code>) [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" h=
ref=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#bib-html" title=3D"HTML Sta=
ndard">HTML<!---0.032930%--></a></cite><!---0.032930%-->], Web Real-Time Co=
mmunications
      (WebRTC; <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"interface" dat=
a-lt=3D"RTCPeerConnection" data-cite=3D"webrtc" data-cite-path=3D"" data-ci=
te-frag=3D"dom-rtcpeerconnection" href=3D"https://www.w3.org/TR/webrtc/#dom=
-rtcpeerconnection"><code>RTCPeerConnection<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!--=
-0.032930%-->) [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D=
"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#bib-webrtc" title=3D"WebRTC: Real=
-Time Communication in Browsers">WEBRTC<!---0.032930%--></a></cite><!---0.0=
32930%-->], media recording
      (<code class=3D"fixme">MediaRecorder</code>) [<cite><a class=3D"bibre=
f" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-mai=
n/#bib-mediastream-recording" title=3D"MediaStream Recording">mediastream-r=
ecording<!---0.032930%--></a></cite><!---0.032930%-->], image capture
      (<code class=3D"fixme">ImageCapture</code>) [<cite><a class=3D"bibref=
" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main=
/#bib-image-capture" title=3D"MediaStream Image Capture">image-capture<!---=
0.032930%--></a></cite><!---0.032930%-->], and web audio
      (<a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"=
MediaStreamAudioSourceNode" data-cite=3D"webaudio" data-cite-path=3D"" data=
-cite-frag=3D"MediaStreamAudioSourceNode" href=3D"https://www.w3.org/TR/web=
audio-1.1/#MediaStreamAudioSourceNode"><code>MediaStreamAudioSourceNode<!--=
-0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%-->) [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-=
link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#bib-w=
ebaudio" title=3D"Web Audio API 1.1">WEBAUDIO<!---0.032930%--></a></cite><!=
---0.032930%-->].</p>
      <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generatedID-0=
"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-0" aria-le=
vel=3D"4"><span>Note</span><!---0.032930%--></div><p class=3D""><a data-xre=
f-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaStream" href=3D"htt=
ps://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream" class=3D"internalDFN=
" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-25"><code>MediaStream<!---0.032930%--></cod=
e></a><!---0.032930%--> consumers must be able to
