t of
              a special purpose algorithm that specifies how the stream id =
must
              be initialized. A good practice is to use a UUID [<cite><a cl=
ass=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/medi=
acapture-main/#bib-rfc4122" title=3D"A Universally Unique IDentifier (UUID)=
 URN Namespace">rfc4122<!---0.032930%--></a></cite><!---0.032930%-->],
              which is 36 characters long in its canonical form. To avoid
              fingerprinting, implementations <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD<=
!---0.032930%--></em> use the forms in section
              4.4 or 4.5 of RFC 4122 when generating UUIDs.</p>
              <p>An example of an algorithm that specifies how the stream i=
d
              must be initialized is the algorithm to associate an incoming
              network component with a <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-lin=
k-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaStream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediac=
apture-main/#dom-mediastream" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-media=
stream-40"><code>MediaStream<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> o=
bject. [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https:/=
/w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#bib-webrtc" title=3D"WebRTC: Real-Time Co=
mmunication in Browsers">WEBRTC<!---0.032930%--></a></cite><!---0.032930%--=
>]</p>
