<code>unmute<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%-->. The reasons for =
a
        <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"Media=
StreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastre=
amtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-54"><code=
>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> to be muted =
are defined by its <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-=
source" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-sour=
ce-1">source</a>.</p>
        <p>For camera and microphone sources, the reasons to <a data-link-t=
ype=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-link-for=3D"source" data-xref-for=3D"source" d=
ata-lt=3D"muted" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-muted=
-0" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-muted-0-2">mute<!---0.032930%--=
></a> are
        <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" data-cite=3D"infra" data-cite-path=3D"" d=
ata-cite-frag=3D"implementation-defined" href=3D"https://infra.spec.whatwg.=
org/#implementation-defined">implementation-defined<!---0.032930%--></a>. T=
his allows user agents to implement privacy
        mitigations in situations like:
        the user pushing a physical mute button on the microphone, the user
        closing a laptop lid with an embedded camera, the user toggling a
        control in the operating system, the user clicking a mute button in=
 the
        <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn=
-user-agent-19">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> chrome, the <a data-link-ty=
pe=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn=
-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-20">User Ag=
ent<!---0.032930%--></a> (on behalf of the user) mutes, etc.</p>
        <p>On some operating systems, microphone access may
        get stolen from the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"h=
ttps://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDF=
N" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-21">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> when an=
other application with higher-audio priority gets access to it,
        for instance in case of an incoming phone call on mobile OS. The <a=
 data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapt=
ure-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agen=
t-22">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD<!---0.03=
2930%--></em> provide
        this information to the web application through <!---0.032930%--><a=
 data-link-type=3D"idl" data-xref-type=3D"attribute|dict-member|const" data=
-link-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"h=
ttps://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastreamtrack-muted" class=
=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-muted-2"><code>muted<!-=
--0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> and
        its associated events.</p>

        <p>Whenever the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https=
://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" i=
d=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-23">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> initiates s=
uch an <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" data-cite=3D"infra" data-cite-path=3D"" da=
ta-cite-frag=3D"implementation-defined" href=3D"https://infra.spec.whatwg.o=
rg/#implementation-defined">implementation-defined<!---0.032930%--></a>
        change for camera or microphone sources, it <em class=3D"rfc2119">M=
UST<!---0.032930%--></em> queue a
        task, using the user interaction task source, to <a data-link-type=
=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-link-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-xref-for=3D"Me=
diaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#set-track-=
muted" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-set-track-muted-1">set a track's=
 muted state<!---0.032930%--></a> to the state desired by the user.</p>
        <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generatedID=
-1"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-1" aria-=
level=3D"6"><span>Note</span><!---0.032930%--></div><div class=3D"">This do=
es not apply to <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-lt=3D"source" hr=
ef=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-source" class=3D"interna=
lDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-source-2">sources<!---0.032930%--></a> defined in
        other specifications. Other specifications need to define their own=
 steps
        to <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-link-for=3D"MediaStre=
amTrack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/m=
ediacapture-main/#set-track-muted" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-set-=
track-muted-2">set a track's muted state<!---0.032930%--></a> if desired.</=
div></div>
        <p>To <dfn class=3D"export abstract-op" data-dfn-for=3D"MediaStream=
Track" id=3D"set-track-muted" data-dfn-type=3D"abstract-op" data-export=3D"=
" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog">set a track's muted state</dfn> t=
o
        <var>newState</var>, the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"inter=
nalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-24">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> <e=
m class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> run the following steps:</p>
        <ol class=3D"algorithm">
          <li>
            <p>Let <var>track</var> be the <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data=
-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.=
io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastreamtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref=
-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-55"><code>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code=
></a><!---0.032930%--> in
            question.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>If <var>track</var>.<!---0.032930%--><a data-xref-type=3D"at=
tribute" data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-link-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" da=
ta-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-lt=3D"[[Muted]]" href=3D"https://w3c.=
github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-muted" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for=
-dfn-muted-1"><code>[[Muted<!---0.032930%-->]]<!---0.032930%--></code></a><=
!---0.032930%--> is already
            <var>newState</var>, then abort these steps.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>Set <var>track</var>.<!---0.032930%--><a data-xref-type=3D"a=
ttribute" data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-link-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" d=
ata-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-lt=3D"[[Muted]]" href=3D"https://w3c=
.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-muted" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-fo=
r-dfn-muted-2"><code>[[Muted<!---0.032930%-->]]<!---0.032930%--></code></a>=
<!---0.032930%--> to
            <var>newState</var>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>If <var>newState</var> is <code>true</code> let
            <var>eventName</var> be <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-t=
ype=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"mute" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-mai=
n/#event-mediastreamtrack-mute" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-event-m=
ediastreamtrack-mute-2"><code>mute<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930=
%-->, otherwise
            <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"u=
nmute" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#event-mediastreamtr=
ack-unmute" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-event-mediastreamtrack-unmu=
te-2"><code>unmute<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%-->.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><a data-link-type=3D"dfn" data-cite=3D"dom" data-cite-path=
=3D"" data-cite-frag=3D"concept-event-fire" href=3D"https://dom.spec.whatwg=
.org/#concept-event-fire">Fire an event<!---0.032930%--></a> named <var>eve=
ntName</var> on
            <var>track</var>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
        <p><dfn data-export=3D"" id=3D"track-enabled" data-dfn-for=3D"Media=
StreamTrack" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn" data-lt=3D"track enabled state|enabled" =
data-lt-nodefault=3D"" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog">Enabled/disa=
bled</dfn> on the other hand is
        available to the application to control (and observe) via the
        <!---0.032930%--><a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-xref-type=3D"attrib=
ute|dict-member|const" data-link-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-xref-for=3D"=
MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-medi=
astreamtrack-enabled" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtr=
ack-enabled-1"><code>enabled<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%-->
        attribute.</p>
        <p>The result for the consumer is the same in the sense that whenev=
er
        <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"Media=
StreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastre=
amtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-56"><code=
>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> is muted or =
disabled (or both) the
        consumer gets zero-information-content, which means silence for aud=
io
        and black frames for video. In other words, media from the source o=
nly
        flows when a <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" dat=
a-lt=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#=
dom-mediastreamtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtr=
ack-57"><code>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%-->=
 object is both
        unmuted and enabled. For example, a video element sourced by a
        <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"Media=
Stream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream" c=
lass=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-53"><code>MediaStream<!-=
--0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> containing only muted or disable=
d <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaStream=
Track" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastreamtrac=
k" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-58"><code>Media=
StreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%-->s
        for audio and video, is playing but rendering black video frames in
        silence.</p>
        <p>For a newly created <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=
=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediaca=
pture-main/#dom-mediastreamtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-m=
ediastreamtrack-59"><code>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---=
0.032930%--> object, the
        following applies: the track is always enabled unless stated otherw=
ise
        (for example when cloned) and the muted state reflects the state of=
 the
        source at the time the track is created.</p>
       </section>
       <section id=3D"life-cycle"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h5 id=3D"x=
4-3-1-2-life-cycle"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.3.1.2<!---0.032930%--> </bdi>Lif=
e-cycle</h5><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacaptu=
re-main/#life-cycle" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.3.1.2"></a></div=
>
       =20
        <p>A <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"=
MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-medi=
astreamtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-60">=
<code>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> has two=
 states in its
        life-cycle: live and ended. A newly created
        <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"Media=
StreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastre=
amtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-61"><code=
>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> can be in ei=
ther state depending
        on how it was created. For example, cloning an ended track results =
in a
        new ended track. The current state is reflected by the object's
        <!---0.032930%--><a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-xref-type=3D"attrib=
ute|dict-member|const" data-link-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-xref-for=3D"=
MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-medi=
astreamtrack-readystate" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastrea=
mtrack-readystate-1"><code>readyState<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032=
930%-->
        attribute.</p>
        <p>In the live state, the track is active and media
        (or zero-information-content if the <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" dat=
a-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github=
.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastreamtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"re=
f-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-62"><code>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></cod=
e></a><!---0.032930%--> is
        <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-link-for=3D"MediaStreamT=
rack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/medi=
acapture-main/#track-muted" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-muted=
-4">muted<!---0.032930%--></a> or <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" dat=
a-link-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-lt=
=3D"enabled" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#track-enabled=
" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-enabled-1">disabled<!---0.03293=
0%--></a>)
        is available for use by consumers.</p>
        <p>If the source is a device exposed by <code>navigator.mediaDevice=
s.<!---0.032930%--></code><!---0.032930%--><a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-x=
ref-type=3D"method" data-link-for=3D"MediaDevices" data-xref-for=3D"MediaDe=
vices" data-lt=3D"getUserMedia()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacaptur=
e-main/#dom-mediadevices-getusermedia" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-=
dom-mediadevices-getusermedia-6"><code>getUserMedia<!---0.032930%--></code>=
</a><code>(<!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%-->)</code><!---=
0.032930%--><!---0.032930%-->,
        then when a track becomes either
        muted or disabled, and this brings all tracks connected to the devi=
ce
        to be either muted, disabled, or stopped, then the UA <em class=3D"=
rfc2119">MAY<!---0.032930%--></em>, using the
        device's <!---0.032930%--><a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-xref-type=
=3D"attribute|dict-member|const" data-link-for=3D"MediaDeviceInfo" data-xre=
f-for=3D"MediaDeviceInfo" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#=
dom-mediadeviceinfo-deviceid" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-media=
deviceinfo-deviceid-2"><code>deviceId<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032=
930%-->, <var>deviceId</var>, set
        <code>navigator.mediaDevices.<!---0.032930%--></code><!---0.032930%=
--><a data-xref-type=3D"attribute" data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-link-f=
or=3D"MediaDevices" data-xref-for=3D"MediaDevices" data-lt=3D"[[devicesLive=
Map]]" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-deviceslivemap"=
 class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-deviceslivemap-2"><code>[[devicesL=
iveMap<!---0.032930%-->]]<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%-->[<var=
>deviceId</var>] to <code>false</code>,
        provided the UA sets it back to <code>true</code> as soon as any
        unstopped track connected to this device becomes un-muted or enable=
d
        again.</p>
        <p>When a "<a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-xref-type=3D"enum-value" =
data-link-for=3D"MediaStreamTrackState" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrackSt=
ate" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#idl-def-MediaStreamTr=
ackState.live" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-idl-def-MediaStreamTrack=
State.live-3"><code>live<!---0.032930%--></code></a>"<!---0.032930%-->, <a =
data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-link-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-=
xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-lt=3D"muted" href=3D"https://w3c.github.=
io/mediacapture-main/#track-muted" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-trac=
k-muted-5">unmuted<!---0.032930%--></a>, and
        <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-link-for=3D"MediaStreamT=
rack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/medi=
acapture-main/#track-enabled" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-ena=
bled-2">enabled<!---0.032930%--></a> track sourced by a device exposed
        by <!---0.032930%--><a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-xref-type=3D"met=
hod" data-link-for=3D"MediaDevices" data-xref-for=3D"MediaDevices" data-lt=
=3D"getUserMedia()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-me=
diadevices-getusermedia" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediadevic=
es-getusermedia-7"><code>getUserMedia<!---0.032930%--></code></a><code>(<!-=
--0.032930%--><!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%-->)</code><!---0.032930%--><!=
---0.032930%--> becomes either
        <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-link-for=3D"MediaStreamT=
rack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/medi=
acapture-main/#track-muted" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-muted=
-6">muted<!---0.032930%--></a> or <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" dat=
a-link-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-lt=
=3D"enabled" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#track-enabled=
" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-enabled-3">disabled<!---0.03293=
0%--></a>,
        and this brings <em>all</em> tracks connected to the device (across=
 all
        <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" data-cite=3D"html" data-cite-path=3D"/doc=
ument-sequences.html" data-cite-frag=3D"navigable" href=3D"https://html.spe=
c.whatwg.org/multipage/document-sequences.html#navigable">navigables<!---0.=
032930%--></a> the user agent operates) to be either
        muted, disabled, or stopped, then the UA <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOU=
LD<!---0.032930%--></em> <dfn id=3D"dfn-relinquish-the-device" tabindex=3D"=
0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">relinquish the device</df=
n>
        within 3 seconds while allowing time for a reasonably-observant use=
r to
        become aware of the transition. The UA <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD=
<!---0.032930%--></em> attempt to reacquire the
        device as soon as any live track sourced by the device
        becomes both <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-link-for=3D=
"MediaStreamTrack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-lt=3D"muted" hre=
f=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#track-muted" class=3D"interna=
lDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-muted-7">unmuted<!---0.032930%--></a> and
        <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-link-for=3D"MediaStreamT=
rack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/medi=
acapture-main/#track-enabled" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-ena=
bled-4">enabled<!---0.032930%--></a> again, provided that track's
        <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" data-cite=3D"html" data-cite-path=3D"/web=
appapis.html" data-cite-frag=3D"concept-relevant-global" href=3D"https://ht=
ml.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/webappapis.html#concept-relevant-global">relev=
ant global object<!---0.032930%--></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" data-cit=
e=3D"html" data-cite-path=3D"/nav-history-apis.html" data-cite-frag=3D"conc=
ept-document-window" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/nav-his=
tory-apis.html#concept-document-window">associated <code>Document<!---0.032=
