                <td>
                  <p>The system <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%-->=
</em> attempt to remove the sound from incoming audio
                  <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-l=
t=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom=
-mediastreamtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack=
-94"><code>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%-->s s=
ourced from WebRTC <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"interface"=
 data-lt=3D"RTCPeerConnection" data-cite=3D"webrtc" data-cite-path=3D"" dat=
a-cite-frag=3D"dom-rtcpeerconnection" href=3D"https://www.w3.org/TR/webrtc/=
#dom-rtcpeerconnection"><code>RTCPeerConnection<!---0.032930%--></code></a>=
<!---0.032930%-->s.</p>
                  This option is useful for cases where it is desirable to
                  transmit locally played audio. One example is a remote mu=
sic
                  class, where a student plays an instrument together with =
some
                  accompaniment produced by a local application. In this ca=
se,
                  the application requires audio coming from the remote par=
ticipant
                  (i.e., the teacher) to be cancelled in order to avoid ech=
o, but
                  also requires that the accompaniment not be cancelled sin=
ce the
                  music teacher on the remote side needs to hear it togethe=
r with
                  the sound from the instrument.<p></p>
                  <p>It is up to the UA to decide which <a data-xref-type=
=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"RTCPeerConnection" data-=
cite=3D"webrtc" data-cite-path=3D"" data-cite-frag=3D"dom-rtcpeerconnection=
" href=3D"https://www.w3.org/TR/webrtc/#dom-rtcpeerconnection"><code>RTCPee=
rConnection<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%-->s to cancel,
                  but the ones being played out by the browsing context cap=
turing
                  microphone <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD<!---0.032930%--><=
/em> be among those cancelled.</p>
                </td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <p>
            In addition to the values from <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data=
-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"EchoCancellationModeEnum" href=3D"https://w3c=
.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-echocancellationmodeenum" class=3D"intern=
alDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-echocancellationmodeenum-5"><code>EchoCancellation=
ModeEnum<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%-->, the <a data-xref-typ=
e=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"echoCancellation" href=3D"htt=
ps://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-echocancellation" class=3D"intern=
alDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-echocancellation-1"><code>echoCancellation<!---0.0=
32930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%-->
            constrainable property also accepts the values <code>true</code=
> and <code>false</code>.
            <code>false</code> means that no echo cancellation will take pl=
ace.
            <code>true</code> means that the UA decides what audio will be =
removed
            from the signals recorded by the microphone. <code>true</code> =
<em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em>
            attempt to cancel at least as much as "<a data-link-type=3D"idl=
" data-xref-type=3D"enum-value" data-link-for=3D"EchoCancellationModeEnum" =
data-xref-for=3D"EchoCancellationModeEnum" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/me=
diacapture-main/#dom-echocancellationmodeenum-remote-only" class=3D"interna=
lDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-echocancellationmodeenum-remote-only-2"><code>remot=
e-only<!---0.032930%--></code></a>"<!---0.032930%-->
            and <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD<!---0.032930%--></em> attempt =
to cancel as much as "<a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-xref-type=3D"enum-valu=
e" data-link-for=3D"EchoCancellationModeEnum" data-xref-for=3D"EchoCancella=
tionModeEnum" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-echocanc=
ellationmodeenum-all" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-echocancellat=
ionmodeenum-all-2"><code>all<!---0.032930%--></code></a>"<!---0.032930%-->.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section id=3D"garbage-collection"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h4 =
id=3D"x4-3-9-garbage-collection"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.3.9<!---0.032930%--=
> </bdi>Garbage Collection</h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.g=
ithub.io/mediacapture-main/#garbage-collection" aria-label=3D"Permalink for=
 Section 4.3.9"></a></div>
       =20
        <p>
          A <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"M=
ediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-media=
streamtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-95"><=
code>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> object <=
em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST NOT<!---0.032930%--></em> be garbage collected if=
 it is
          not <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-link-for=3D"MediaS=
treamTrack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.i=
o/mediacapture-main/#track-ended" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track=
-ended-12">ended<!---0.032930%--></a> and there are any event listeners
          registered for <a data-lt=3D"muted" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/mediacapture-main/#event-mediastreamtrack-mute" class=3D"internalDFN" data=
-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-event-mediastreamtrack-mute-4">mute</a>, <=
a data-lt=3D"unmuted" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#even=
t-mediastreamtrack-unmute" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=
=3D"ref-for-event-mediastreamtrack-unmute-4">unmute</a>
          or <a data-lt=3D"ended" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacaptur=
e-main/#event-mediastreamtrack-ended" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=
=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-event-mediastreamtrack-ended-2">ended</a> events.
          <!-- FIXME: add configurationchange event -->
          Each source type can further refine the garbage collection rules =
as
          sources may never fire a particular event.
          </p><div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-9"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-9"=
 aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span><!---0.032930%--></div><div class=3D"">
             Authors are encouraged to call stop() on <a data-xref-type=3D"=
_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://=
w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastreamtrack" class=3D"internalDFN=
" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-96"><code>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.03293=
0%--></code></a><!---0.032930%-->,
             especially capture tracks since the underlying resource are co=
stly
             and it can have effects on the privacy indicators presented to=
 the user.
          </div></div>
        <p></p>
      </section>
