       =20
        <dl data-link-for=3D"OverconstrainedError" data-dfn-for=3D"Overcons=
trainedError" class=3D"constructors">
          <dt><dfn data-idl=3D"interface" data-export=3D"" data-dfn-type=3D=
"interface" id=3D"dom-overconstrainederror" data-title=3D"OverconstrainedEr=
ror" data-dfn-for=3D"" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog"><code>Overco=
nstrainedError</code></dfn></dt>
          <dd>
            <p>Run the following steps:</p>
            <ol class=3D"algorithm">
              <li>
                <p>Let <var>constraint</var> be the constructor's first
                argument.</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>Let <var>message</var> be the constructor's second argum=
ent.
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>Let <var>e</var> be a new
                <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=
=3D"OverconstrainedError" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#=
dom-overconstrainederror" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-overconst=
rainederror-2"><code>OverconstrainedError<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0=
.032930%--> object.</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>Invoke the <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D=
"interface" data-lt=3D"DOMException" data-cite=3D"webidl" data-cite-path=3D=
"" data-cite-frag=3D"idl-DOMException" href=3D"https://webidl.spec.whatwg.o=
rg/#idl-DOMException"><code>DOMException<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.=
032930%--> constructor of
                <var>e</var> with the <code>message</code> argument set to
                <var>message</var> and the <code>name</code> argument set t=
o
                <code>"OverconstrainedError"</code>.</p>
                <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gen=
eratedID-14"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note=
-14" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span><!---0.032930%--></div><p class=3D""=
>This name does not have a mapping to a legacy
                code so <var>e</var>'s <code>code</code> attribute will ret=
urn
                0.</p></div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>Set <var>e.constraint</var> to <var>constraint</var>.</p=
>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>Return <var>e</var>.</p>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </dd>
        </dl>
      </section>
