              documents, <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> f=
ollow the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.=
io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-d=
fn-user-agent-66">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a>'s partitioning rules for
              storage (such as <!---0.032930%--><a data-link-type=3D"attrib=
ute" data-xref-type=3D"attribute|dict-member|const" data-link-for=3D"Window=
LocalStorage" data-xref-for=3D"WindowLocalStorage" data-cite=3D"html" data-=
cite-path=3D"/webstorage.html" data-cite-frag=3D"dom-localstorage" href=3D"=
https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/webstorage.html#dom-localstorage"><c=
ode>localStorage<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%-->), if any,
              to not interfere with mitigations for cross-site correlation.
              If the identifier can uniquely
              identify the user, then it <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.0=
32930%--></em> be un-guessable in documents from
              other origins to prevent the identifier from being used to
              correlate the same user across different origins. An identifi=
er
              can be reused across origins as long as it is not tied to the=
 user
              and can be guessed by other means, like the User-Agent string=
.</p>
              <p>If any local devices have been attached to a live
              <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D=
"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-med=
iastreamtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-114=
"><code>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> in a =
page from this origin, or <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"htt=
ps://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#stored-permissions" class=3D"internal=
DFN" id=3D"ref-for-stored-permissions-1">stored permission<!---0.032930%-->=
</a> to access local
              devices has been granted to this origin, then this identifier
              <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> be persisted=
, except as detailed below. Unique and stable
              identifiers let the application save, identify the availabili=
ty
              of, and directly request specific sources, across multiple
              visits.</p>
              <p>However, as long as no local device has been attached to a
              live MediaStreamTrack in a page from this origin, and no <a d=
ata-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacaptur=
e-main/#stored-permissions" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-stored-perm=
issions-2">stored permission<!---0.032930%--></a> to access local
              devices has been granted to this origin, then the <a data-lin=
k-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/=
#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-67">Use=
r Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY<!---0.032930%--></em=
>
              clear this identifier once the last browsing session from thi=
s
              origin has been closed. If the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstr=
act-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" cl=
ass=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-68">User Agent<!---0.03293=
0%--></a> chooses not to clear
              the identifier in this condition, then it <em class=3D"rfc211=
9">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> provide for the
              user to visibly inspect and delete the identifier, like a
              cookie.</p>
              <p class=3D"fingerprint">Since <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" da=
ta-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"deviceId" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/med=
iacapture-main/#dom-mediadeviceinfo-deviceid" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"r=
ef-for-dom-mediadeviceinfo-deviceid-12"><code>deviceId<!---0.032930%--></co=
de></a><!---0.032930%--> may persist
              across browsing sessions and to reduce its potential as a
              fingerprinting mechanism, <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-li=
nk-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"deviceId" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacap=
ture-main/#dom-mediadeviceinfo-deviceid" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-fo=
r-dom-mediadeviceinfo-deviceid-13"><code>deviceId<!---0.032930%--></code></=
a><!---0.032930%--> is to be treated
              as other persistent storage mechanisms such as cookies
              [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"=
https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#bib-cookies" title=3D"HTTP State M=
anagement Mechanism">COOKIES<!---0.032930%--></a></cite><!---0.032930%-->],=
 in that <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.i=
o/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-df=
n-user-agent-69">User Agents<!---0.032930%--></a> <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUS=
T NOT<!---0.032930%--></em> persist device
              identifiers for sites that are blocked from using cookies, an=
d
              <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.git=
hub.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-f=
or-dfn-user-agent-70">User Agents<!---0.032930%--></a> <em class=3D"rfc2119=
">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> rotate per-origin device identifiers when othe=
r
              persistent storage are cleared.<img src=3D"https://w3c.github=
.io/mediacapture-main/images/fingerprint.png" alt=3D"(This is a fingerprint=
ing vector.)" width=3D"15" height=3D"21"></p>
            </dd>
            <dt id=3D"def-mediadeviceinfo-kind"><dfn data-export=3D"" data-=
dfn-type=3D"attribute" id=3D"dom-mediadeviceinfo-kind" data-idl=3D"attribut=
e" data-title=3D"kind" data-dfn-for=3D"MediaDeviceInfo" data-type=3D"MediaD=
eviceKind" data-lt=3D"kind" data-local-lt=3D"MediaDeviceInfo.kind" tabindex=
=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog"><code>kind</code></dfn> of
            type <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=
=3D"MediaDeviceKind" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-m=
ediadevicekind" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediadevicekind-4">=
<code>MediaDeviceKind<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%-->,
            readonly</dt>
            <dd>
              <p>The kind of the represented device.</p>
            </dd>
            <dt><dfn data-export=3D"" data-dfn-type=3D"attribute" id=3D"dom=
-mediadeviceinfo-label" data-idl=3D"attribute" data-title=3D"label" data-df=
n-for=3D"MediaDeviceInfo" data-type=3D"DOMString" data-lt=3D"label" data-lo=
cal-lt=3D"MediaDeviceInfo.label" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog"><c=
ode>label</code></dfn> of type <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=
=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"DOMString" data-cite=3D"webidl" data-cite-path=3D=
"" data-cite-frag=3D"idl-DOMString" href=3D"https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/=
#idl-DOMString"><code>DOMString<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--=
>, readonly</dt>
            <dd>
              <p>A label describing this device (for example "External USB
              Webcam"). This label is intended to allow the end user to tel=
l the
              difference between devices. Applications can=E2=80=99t assume=
 that the
              label contains any specific information, such as the device t=
ype or model.
              If the device has no associated label, then this
              attribute <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> re=
turn the empty string.</p>
            </dd>
            <dt id=3D"def-mediadeviceinfo-groupId"><dfn data-export=3D"" da=
ta-dfn-type=3D"attribute" id=3D"dom-mediadeviceinfo-groupid" data-idl=3D"at=
tribute" data-title=3D"groupId" data-dfn-for=3D"MediaDeviceInfo" data-type=
=3D"DOMString" data-lt=3D"groupId" data-local-lt=3D"MediaDeviceInfo.groupId=
" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog"><code>groupId</code></dfn>
            of type <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"interface=
" data-lt=3D"DOMString" data-cite=3D"webidl" data-cite-path=3D"" data-cite-=
frag=3D"idl-DOMString" href=3D"https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#idl-DOMStrin=
g"><code>DOMString<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%-->, readonly</=
dt>
            <dd>
              <p>The group identifier of the represented device. Two device=
s
              have the same group identifier if they belong to the same
              physical device. For example, the audio input and output devi=
ces
              representing the speaker and microphone of the same headset
              have the same groupId.</p>
              <p>The group identifier <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.0329=
30%--></em> be uniquely generated for each
              <a data-cite=3D"dom" data-cite-path=3D"" data-cite-frag=3D"co=
ncept-document" data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://dom.spec.whatwg.org/=
#concept-document">document</a>.</p>
            </dd>
          </dl>
        </section>
