  <section id=3D"local-content"><!--OddPage--><div class=3D"header-wrapper"=
><h2 id=3D"x10-obtaining-local-multimedia-content"><bdi class=3D"secno">10.=
<!---0.032930%--> </bdi>Obtaining local multimedia content</h2><a class=3D"=
self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#local-content" =
aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 10."></a></div>
   =20
    <p>This section extends <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"i=
nterface" data-lt=3D"Navigator" data-cite=3D"html" data-cite-path=3D"/syste=
m-state.html" data-cite-frag=3D"navigator" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg=
.org/multipage/system-state.html#navigator"><code>Navigator<!---0.032930%--=
></code></a><!---0.032930%--> and
    <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaDevi=
ces" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediadevices" cla=
ss=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediadevices-17"><code>MediaDevices<!-=
--0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> with APIs to request permission =
to access
    media input devices available to the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-=
op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=
=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-72">User Agent<!---0.032930%-=
-></a>.</p>
    <p>Alternatively, a local <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D=
"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaStream" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-ma=
in/#dom-mediastream" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-90=
"><code>MediaStream<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> can be cap=
tured
    from certain types of DOM elements, such as the video element
    [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://w3=
c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#bib-mediacapture-fromelement" title=3D"Media=
 Capture from DOM Elements">mediacapture-fromelement<!---0.032930%--></a></=
cite><!---0.032930%-->]. This can be useful for automated testing.</p>
