wrapper"><h3 id=3D"x10-1-mediadevices-interface-extensions"><bdi class=3D"s=
ecno">10.1<!---0.032930%--> </bdi><a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-typ=
e=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaDevices" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacaptu=
re-main/#dom-mediadevices" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediadev=
ices-18"><code>MediaDevices<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> In=
terface Extensions</h3><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/mediacapture-main/#mediadevices-interface-extensions" aria-label=3D"Permal=
ink for Section 10.1"></a></div>
     =20
      <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generatedID-2=
1"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-21" aria-=
level=3D"4"><span>Note</span><!---0.032930%--></div><div class=3D"">
        The definition of <!---0.032930%--><a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-x=
ref-type=3D"method" data-link-for=3D"Navigator" data-xref-for=3D"Navigator"=
 data-lt=3D"getUserMedia()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main=
/#dom-navigator-getusermedia" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-navig=
ator-getusermedia-1"><code>getUserMedia<!---0.032930%--></code></a><code>(<=
!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%-->)</code><!---0.032930%-->=
<!---0.032930%--> in this section reflects two major
        changes from the method definition that has existed under <a data-x=
ref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"Navigator" data-=
cite=3D"html" data-cite-path=3D"/system-state.html" data-cite-frag=3D"navig=
ator" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/system-state.html#navi=
gator"><code>Navigator<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> for
        many months.
        <p>First, the official definition for the <!---0.032930%--><a data-=
link-type=3D"idl" data-xref-type=3D"method" data-link-for=3D"MediaDevices" =
data-xref-for=3D"MediaDevices" data-lt=3D"getUserMedia()" href=3D"https://w=
3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediadevices-getusermedia" class=3D"int=
ernalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediadevices-getusermedia-21"><code>getUserMedi=
a<!---0.032930%--></code></a><code>(<!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%--><!---=
0.032930%-->)</code><!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%--> method, and
        the one which developers are encouraged to use, is now the one defi=
ned
        here under <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-=
lt=3D"MediaDevices" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-me=
diadevices" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediadevices-19"><code>=
MediaDevices<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%-->. This decision re=
flected consensus as long as
        the original API remained available at <a href=3D"https://w3c.githu=
b.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-navigator-getusermedia" class=3D"internalDFN" d=
ata-link-type=3D"idl" id=3D"ref-for-dom-navigator-getusermedia-2"><code>Nav=
igator.getUserMedia</code></a>
        under the <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"interface" =
data-lt=3D"Navigator" data-cite=3D"html" data-cite-path=3D"/system-state.ht=
ml" data-cite-frag=3D"navigator" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multi=
page/system-state.html#navigator"><code>Navigator<!---0.032930%--></code></=
a><!---0.032930%--> object for backwards compatibility reasons, since
        the working group acknowledges that early users of these APIs have =
been
        encouraged to define getUserMedia as "var getUserMedia =3D
        navigator.getUserMedia || navigator.webkitGetUserMedia ||
        navigator.mozGetUserMedia;" in order for their code to be functiona=
l
        both before and after official implementations of getUserMedia() in
        popular <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.g=
ithub.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref=
-for-dfn-user-agent-73">User Agents<!---0.032930%--></a>. To ensure functio=
nal equivalence, the getUserMedia()
        method under <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"interfac=
e" data-lt=3D"Navigator" data-cite=3D"html" data-cite-path=3D"/system-state=
.html" data-cite-frag=3D"navigator" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/mu=
ltipage/system-state.html#navigator"><code>Navigator<!---0.032930%--></code=
></a><!---0.032930%--> is defined in terms of the method here.</p>
        <p>Second, the method defined here is Promises-based, while the one
        defined under <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"interfa=
ce" data-lt=3D"Navigator" data-cite=3D"html" data-cite-path=3D"/system-stat=
e.html" data-cite-frag=3D"navigator" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/m=
ultipage/system-state.html#navigator"><code>Navigator<!---0.032930%--></cod=
e></a><!---0.032930%--> is currently still callback-based. Developers
        expecting to find getUserMedia() defined under Navigator are strong=
ly
        encouraged to read the detailed Note given there.</p>
      </div></div>
      <p>The <!---0.032930%--><a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-xref-type=3D"a=
ttribute|dict-member|const" data-link-for=3D"MediaDevices" data-xref-for=3D=
"MediaDevices" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediade=
vices-getsupportedconstraints" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-medi=
adevices-getsupportedconstraints-1"><code>getSupportedConstraints<!---0.032=
