                      value "<a data-link-type=3D"exception" data-cite=3D"w=
ebidl" data-xref-type=3D"exception" data-cite-path=3D"" data-cite-frag=3D"n=
otallowederror" href=3D"https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#notallowederror"><c=
ode>NotAllowedError<!---0.032930%--></code></a>"<!---0.032930%-->.</p>
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>Return <var>p</var>.</p>
                </li>
              </ol>
            </dd>
          </dl>
        </section>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p>To check whether <dfn class=3D"abstract-op" id=3D"getUserMedia-s=
pecific-failure-is-allowed" data-dfn-type=3D"abstract-op" tabindex=3D"0" ar=
ia-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-export=3D"">getUserMedia specific failure is al=
lowed</dfn>,
        given <var>requestedMediaTypes</var>, run the following steps:</p>
        <ol class=3D"algorithm">
          <li><p>If <var>requestedMediaTypes</var> contains "audio", read t=
he <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" data-cite=3D"permissions" data-cite-path=3D"" =
data-cite-frag=3D"dfn-permission-state" href=3D"https://www.w3.org/TR/permi=
ssions/#dfn-permission-state">permission state<!---0.032930%--></a>
            for the descriptor whose name is "microphone". If the result of=
 the request is
            "<a data-link-type=3D"enum-value" data-xref-type=3D"enum-value"=
 data-link-for=3D"PermissionState" data-xref-for=3D"PermissionState" data-c=
ite=3D"permissions" data-cite-path=3D"" data-cite-frag=3D"dom-permissionsta=
te-denied" href=3D"https://www.w3.org/TR/permissions/#dom-permissionstate-d=
enied"><code>denied<!---0.032930%--></code></a>"<!---0.032930%-->, return <=
code>false</code>.</p></li>
         <li><p>If <var>requestedMediaTypes</var> contains "video", read th=
e <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" data-cite=3D"permissions" data-cite-path=3D"" d=
ata-cite-frag=3D"dfn-permission-state" href=3D"https://www.w3.org/TR/permis=
sions/#dfn-permission-state">permission state<!---0.032930%--></a>
            for the descriptor whose name is "camera". If the result of the=
 request is
            "<a data-link-type=3D"enum-value" data-xref-type=3D"enum-value"=
 data-link-for=3D"PermissionState" data-xref-for=3D"PermissionState" data-c=
ite=3D"permissions" data-cite-path=3D"" data-cite-frag=3D"dom-permissionsta=
te-denied" href=3D"https://www.w3.org/TR/permissions/#dom-permissionstate-d=
enied"><code>denied<!---0.032930%--></code></a>"<!---0.032930%-->, return <=
code>false</code>.</p></li>
         <li><p>Return <code>true</code>.</p></li>
        </ol>
      </div>
      <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generatedID-2=
5"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-25" aria-=
level=3D"4"><span>Note</span><!---0.032930%--></div><div class=3D"">
        <p>In the algorithm above, constraints are checked twice - once at
        device selection, and once after access approval. Time may have pas=
sed
        between those checks, so it is conceivable that the selected device=
 is
        no longer suitable. In this case, a NotReadableError will result.</=
p>
      </div></div>
