    <section class=3D"informative" id=3D"implementation-suggestions"><div c=
lass=3D"header-wrapper"><h3 id=3D"x10-4-implementation-suggestions"><bdi cl=
ass=3D"secno">10.4<!---0.032930%--> </bdi>Implementation Suggestions</h3><a=
 class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#imple=
mentation-suggestions" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 10.4"></a></div>=
<p><em>This section is non-normative.<!---0.032930%--></em></p>
     =20
      <div class=3D"practice advisement"><a class=3D"marker self-link" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#resource-reservation"><bdi lan=
g=3D"en">Best Practice <!---0.032930%-->1<!---0.032930%--></bdi></a><!---0.=
032930%-->: <span class=3D"practicelab" id=3D"resource-reservation">Resourc=
e
        reservation</span><!---0.032930%-->
       =20
        <p class=3D"practicedesc">The <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op"=
 href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"=
internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-88">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></=
a> is encouraged to reserve
        resources when it has determined that a given call to
        <!---0.032930%--><a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-xref-type=3D"method=
" data-link-for=3D"MediaDevices" data-xref-for=3D"MediaDevices" data-lt=3D"=
getUserMedia()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediad=
evices-getusermedia" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediadevices-g=
etusermedia-27"><code>getUserMedia<!---0.032930%--></code></a><code>(<!---0=
.032930%--><!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%-->)</code><!---0.032930%--><!---=
0.032930%--> will be successful. It is preferable
        to reserve the resource prior to resolving the returned promise.
        Subsequent calls to <!---0.032930%--><a data-link-type=3D"idl" data=
-xref-type=3D"method" data-link-for=3D"MediaDevices" data-xref-for=3D"Media=
Devices" data-lt=3D"getUserMedia()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapt=
ure-main/#dom-mediadevices-getusermedia" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-fo=
r-dom-mediadevices-getusermedia-28"><code>getUserMedia<!---0.032930%--></co=
de></a><code>(<!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%-->)</code><!=
---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%-->
        (in this page or any other) should treat the resource that was
        previously allocated, as well as resources held by other applicatio=
ns,
        as busy. Resources marked as busy should not be provided as sources=
 to
        the current web page, unless specified by the user. Optionally, the
        <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn=
-user-agent-89">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> may choose to provide a str=
eam sourced from a busy source
        but only to a page whose origin matches the owner of the original
        stream that is keeping the source busy.</p>
        <p class=3D"practicedesc">This document recommends that in the perm=
ission
        grant dialog or device selection interface (if one is present), the
        user be allowed to select any available hardware as a source for th=
e
        stream requested by the page (provided the resource is able to fulf=
ill
        any specified <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#d=
fn-required-constraints" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D=
"ref-for-dfn-required-constraints-9">required constraints</a>). Although no=
t specifically
        recommended as best practice, note that some <a data-link-type=3D"d=
fn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-a=
gent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-90">User Agents<!-=
--0.032930%--></a> may support
        the ability to substitute a video or audio source with local files =
and
        other media. A file picker may be used to provide this functionalit=
y to
        the user.</p>
        <p class=3D"practicedesc">This document also recommends that the us=
er be
        shown all resources that are currently busy as a result of prior ca=
lls
        to <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediadev=
ices-getusermedia" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediadevices-getusermedia-29">getUserM=
edia()</a> (in this
        page or any other page that is still alive) and be allowed to termi=
nate
        that stream and utilize the resource for the current page instead. =
If
        possible in the current operating environment, it is also suggested
        that resources currently held by other applications be presented an=
d
        treated in the same manner. If the user chooses this option, the tr=
ack
        corresponding to the resource that was provided to the page whose
        stream was affected must be removed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class=3D"practice advisement"><a class=3D"marker self-link" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#stored-permissions" id=3D"ref-=
for-stored-permissions-3"><bdi lang=3D"en">Best Practice <!---0.032930%-->2=
<!---0.032930%--></bdi></a><!---0.032930%-->: <dfn id=3D"stored-permissions=
" class=3D"practicelab" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-ty=
pe=3D"dfn">Stored
        Permission</dfn><!---0.032930%-->
        s
        <p class=3D"practicedesc">When permission is requested for a device=
, the
        <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn=
-user-agent-91">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> may choose to store this pe=
rmission for later use by the same origin, so that
        the user does not need to grant permission again at a later time.
        It is a <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.g=
ithub.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref=
-for-dfn-user-agent-92">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> choice whether it o=
ffers functionality to store
        permission to each device separately, all devices of a given class,=
 or
        all devices; the choice needs to be apparent to the user, and
        permission must have been granted for the entire set whose permissi=
on
        is being stored, e.g., to store permission to use all cameras the u=
ser
        must have given permission to use all cameras and not just one.</p>
        <p class=3D"practicedesc">As described, this specification does not
        dictate whether or not granting permission results in a stored
        permission. When permission is not stored, permission will last onl=
y
        until such time as all MediaStreamTracks sourced from that device h=
ave
        been stopped.</p>
      </div>
      <div class=3D"practice advisement"><a class=3D"marker self-link" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#handling-devices"><bdi lang=3D=
"en">Best Practice <!---0.032930%-->3<!---0.032930%--></bdi></a><!---0.0329=
30%-->: <span class=3D"practicelab" id=3D"handling-devices">Handling multip=
le
        devices</span><!---0.032930%-->
       =20
        <p class=3D"practicedesc">A <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediac=
apture-main/#dom-mediastream" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"idl" =
id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastream-104"><code>MediaStream</code></a> may contain=
 more than one
        video and audio track. This makes it possible to include video from=
 two
        or more webcams in a single stream object, for example. However, th=
e
        current API does not allow a page to express a need for multiple vi=
deo
        streams from independent sources.</p>
        <p class=3D"practicedesc">It is recommended for multiple calls to
        <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediadevice=
s-getusermedia" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediadevices-getusermedia-30">getUserMedi=
a()</a> from the
        same page to be allowed as a way for pages to request multiple disc=
rete
        video and/or audio streams.</p>
        <p class=3D"practicedesc">Note also that if multiple <a href=3D"htt=
ps://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediadevices-getusermedia" id=3D"=
ref-for-dom-mediadevices-getusermedia-31">getUserMedia()</a> calls are done=
 by a
        page, the order in which they request resources, and the order in w=
hich
        they complete, is not constrained by this specification.</p>
        <p class=3D"practicedesc">A single call to <a href=3D"https://w3c.g=
ithub.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediadevices-getusermedia" id=3D"ref-for-do=
m-mediadevices-getusermedia-32">getUserMedia()</a> will always return
        a stream with either zero or one audio tracks, and either zero or o=
ne
        video tracks. If a script calls <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/me=
diacapture-main/#dom-mediadevices-getusermedia" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediadevi=
ces-getusermedia-33">getUserMedia()</a> multiple times
        before reaching a stable state, this document advises the UI design=
er
        that the permission dialogs should be merged, so that the user can =
give
        permission for the use of multiple cameras and/or media sources in =
one
        dialog interaction. The constraints on each getUserMedia call can b=
e
        used to decide which stream gets which media sources.</p>
      </div>
      <div class=3D"practice advisement"><a class=3D"marker self-link" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#generating-deviceids"><bdi lan=
g=3D"en">Best Practice <!---0.032930%-->4<!---0.032930%--></bdi></a><!---0.=
032930%-->: <span class=3D"practicelab" id=3D"generating-deviceids">Generat=
ing deviceIds</span><!---0.032930%-->
       =20
        <p class=3D"practicedesc">An efficient practice for generating a
        <!---0.032930%--><a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-xref-type=3D"attrib=
ute|dict-member|const" data-link-for=3D"MediaDeviceInfo" data-xref-for=3D"M=
ediaDeviceInfo" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediad=
eviceinfo-deviceid" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediadeviceinfo=
-deviceid-15"><code>deviceId<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> i=
s to generate a cryptographic hash from
        a private key + (origin or origin + top-level origin, based on the =
user
        agents' partitioning rules) + salt + device's underlying (hardware)=
 id
        in the driver, and present the resulting hash as an alphanumeric st=
ring.
        Using 32 bits or fewer for the hash is recommended, but not much lo=
wer,
        to avoid risk of collision.
        </p>
        <p class=3D"practicedesc">A lower-entropy alternative, at the cost =
of
        storage, is to assign the numbers 0 through 255 randomly to each
        new device encountered for each origin or origin + top-level origin=
,
        based on the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://=
w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-93">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a>'s partitioni=
ng rules, retiring the number that
        hasn't been seen the longest if numbers run out.</p>
      </div>
      <div class=3D"practice advisement"><a class=3D"marker self-link" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#muting-devices"><bdi lang=3D"e=
n">Best Practice <!---0.032930%-->5<!---0.032930%--></bdi></a><!---0.032930=
%-->: <span class=3D"practicelab" id=3D"muting-devices">Device muting initi=
ated by <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn=
-user-agent-94">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a></span><!---0.032930%-->
       =20
        <p class=3D"practicedesc">A track sourced by a camera or microphone=
 may be
        forcibly <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-link-for=3D"Med=
iaStreamTrack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.githu=
b.io/mediacapture-main/#track-muted" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-tr=
ack-muted-11">muted<!---0.032930%--></a> by a <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abst=
ract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" c=
lass=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-95">User Agent<!---0.0329=
30%--></a> at any time, in order
        to manage a user's privacy. However, doing so may create web
        compatibility issues, as well as leak information about user activi=
ty, so
        caution is advised.
        </p>
        <p class=3D"practicedesc">Best practice is to
        <a data-lt=3D"muted" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-mai=
n/#event-mediastreamtrack-mute" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn=
" id=3D"ref-for-event-mediastreamtrack-mute-5">mute</a> a camera or microph=
one track in the following
        instances:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <p>An OS-level event for which the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abs=
tract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" =
class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-96">User Agent<!---0.032=
930%--></a> already suspends media
            playback globally, but JavaScript is not suspended. The rationa=
le is
            users may otherwise be surprised if capture were to continue in=
 this
            situation (unless they've intentionally configured it this way)=
.
            If the OS-level event already causes frames to stop coming in
            on the track, then no new information of user activity is revea=
led
            by this. Even when this is not the case, revealing that capture=
 is
            ending seems like a reasonable privacy tradeoff compared to
            continuing capture in situations that may surprise users.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>A web page not <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-li=
nk-for=3D"Document" data-xref-for=3D"Document" data-lt=3D"is in view" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-is-in-view" class=3D"inter=
nalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-is-in-view-8">in view<!---0.032930%--></a>
            <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-link-for=3D"MediaStr=
eamTrack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-lt=3D"enabled" href=3D"ht=
tps://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#track-enabled" class=3D"internalDFN"=
 id=3D"ref-for-track-enabled-6">re-enables<!---0.032930%--></a> a track whe=
n all tracks from that
            source are <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-link-for=
=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-lt=3D"enabled=
" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#track-enabled" class=3D"=
internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-enabled-7">disabled<!---0.032930%--></a>, =
in order to delay
            resumption of capture until the page <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|a=
bstract-op" data-link-for=3D"Document" data-xref-for=3D"Document" href=3D"h=
ttps://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-is-in-view" class=3D"internalDF=
N" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-is-in-view-9">is in view<!---0.032930%--></a>.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class=3D"practicedesc">Best practice is to
        <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-link-for=3D"MediaStreamT=
rack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-lt=3D"muted" href=3D"https://=
w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#track-muted" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"r=
ef-for-track-muted-12">unmute<!---0.032930%--></a> a camera or microphone t=
rack it previously
        <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-link-for=3D"MediaStreamT=
rack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/medi=
acapture-main/#track-muted" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-muted=
-13">muted<!---0.032930%--></a>, in the following instances:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <p>An OS-level event for which the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abs=
tract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" =
class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-97">User Agent<!---0.032=
930%--></a> already resumes media
            playback globally, <em>and</em> the page is visible to the user
            (e.g. not during a lock screen). <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstr=
act-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" cl=
ass=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-98">User Agents<!---0.0329=
30%--></a> may defer such action
            if it determines significant time has passed that may jeopardiz=
e a
            user's awareness of the earlier capture session.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>A web page comes <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-=
link-for=3D"Document" data-xref-for=3D"Document" data-lt=3D"is in view" hre=
f=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-is-in-view" class=3D"inte=
rnalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-is-in-view-10">into view<!---0.032930%--></a> an=
d
            has one or more <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-link=
-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https:=
//w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#track-enabled" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-track-enabled-8">enabled<!---0.032930%--></a> tracks that are a=
lso
            <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-link-for=3D"MediaStr=
eamTrack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/=
mediacapture-main/#track-muted" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-m=
uted-14">muted<!---0.032930%--></a>.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>
  <section id=3D"constrainable-interface"><!--OddPage--><div class=3D"heade=
r-wrapper"><h2 id=3D"x11-constrainable-pattern"><bdi class=3D"secno">11.<!-=
--0.032930%--> </bdi>Constrainable Pattern</h2><a class=3D"self-link" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#constrainable-interface" aria-=
label=3D"Permalink for Section 11."></a></div>
   =20
    <p>The Constrainable pattern allows applications to inspect and adjust =
the
    properties of objects implementing it (the <dfn id=3D"dfn-constrainable=
-object" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">cons=
trainable
    object</dfn>). It is broken out as a separate set of definitions so tha=
t it
    can be referred to by other specifications. The core concept is the
    Capability, which consists of a constrainable property of an object and=
 the
    set of its possible values, which may be specified either as a range or=
 as
    an enumeration. For example, a camera might be capable of framerates (a
    property) between 20 and 50 frames per second (a range) and may be able=
 to
    be positioned (a property) facing towards the user, away from the user,=
 or
    to the left or right of the user (an enumerated set). The application c=
an
    examine a constrainable property's supported Capabilities via the
    <code>getCapabilities()</code> accessor.</p>
    <p>The application can select the (range of) values it wants for an
    object's Capabilities by means of basic and/or advanced ConstraintSets =
and
    the <code>applyConstraints()</code> method. A ConstraintSet consists of=
 the
    names of one or more properties of the object plus the desired value (o=
r a
    range of desired values) for each property. Each of those property/valu=
e
    pairs can be considered to be an individual constraint. For example, th=
e
    application may set a ConstraintSet containing two constraints, the fir=
st
    stating that the framerate of a camera be between 30 and 40 frames per
    second (a range) and the second that the camera should be facing the us=
er
    (a specific value). How the individual constraints interact depends on
    whether and how they are given in the basic Constraint structure, which=
 is
    a ConstraintSet with an additional 'advanced' property, or whether they=
 are
    in a ConstraintSet in the advanced list. The behavior is as follows: al=
l
    'min', 'max', and 'exact' constraints in the basic Constraint structure=
 are
    together treated as the <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-m=
ain/#dfn-required-constraints" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn"=
 id=3D"ref-for-dfn-required-constraints-10">required constraints</a>, and i=
f it is not possible
    to satisfy simultaneously all of those individual constraints for the
    indicated property names, the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" hre=
f=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"inte=
rnalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-99">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> <=
em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" d=
ata-cite=3D"webidl" data-cite-path=3D"" data-cite-frag=3D"reject" href=3D"h=
ttps://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#reject">reject<!---0.032930%--></a> the retu=
rned
    promise. Otherwise, it must apply the required constraints. Next, it wi=
ll
    consider any ConstraintSets given in the
    <code><a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-constrain=
ts-advanced" id=3D"ref-for-dom-constraints-advanced-2">advanced</a></code> =
list, in the
    order in which they are specified, and will try to satisfy/apply each c=
omplete
    ConstraintSet (i.e., all constraints in the ConstraintSet together), bu=
t
    will skip a ConstraintSet if and only if it cannot satisfy/apply it in =
its
    entirety. Next, the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https=
://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" i=
d=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-100">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> <em class=
=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> attempt to apply, individually, any
    'ideal' constraints or a constraint given as a bare value for the prope=
rty
    (referred to as <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn=
-optional-basic-constraints" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" i=
d=3D"ref-for-dfn-optional-basic-constraints-1">optional basic constraints</=
a>).
    Of these properties, it <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em=
> satisfy the largest number that it can, in any
    order. Finally, the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https=
://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" i=
d=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-101">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> <em class=
=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" data-cite=
=3D"webidl" data-cite-path=3D"" data-cite-frag=3D"resolve" href=3D"https://=
webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#resolve">resolve<!---0.032930%--></a> the returned
    promise.</p>
    <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generatedID-27"=
><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-27" aria-le=
vel=3D"3"><span>Note</span><!---0.032930%--></div><div class=3D"">
      Any constraint provided via this API will only be considered if the g=
iven
      constrainable property is supported by the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|a=
bstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent=
" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-102">User Agent<!---0.=
032930%--></a>. JavaScript
      application code is expected to first check, via
      <code>getSupportedConstraints()</code>, that all the named properties
      that are used are supported by the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-=
op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=
=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-103">User Agent<!---0.032930%=
--></a>. The reason for this is that
      WebIDL drops any unsupported names from the dictionary holding the
      constraints, so the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"htt=
ps://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN"=
 id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-104">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> does not=
 see them and the unsupported names
      end up being silently ignored. This will cause confusing programming
      errors as the JavaScript code will be setting constraints but the <a =
data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacaptu=
re-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent=
-105">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a>
      will be ignoring them. <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"=
https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalD=
FN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-106">User Agents<!---0.032930%--></a> that=
 support (recognize) the name of a
      required constraint but cannot satisfy it will generate an error, whi=
le
      <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/m=
ediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-u=
ser-agent-107">User Agents<!---0.032930%--></a> that do not support the con=
strainable property will not generate
      an error.
    </div></div>
    <p>The following examples may help to understand how constraints work. =
The
    first shows a basic Constraint structure. Three constraints are given, =
each
    of which the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.=
github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"re=
f-for-dfn-user-agent-108">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> will attempt to s=
atisfy individually. Depending
    upon the resolutions available for this camera, it is possible that not=
 all
    three constraints can be satisfied at the same time. If so, the <a data=
-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-m=
ain/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-109=
">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a>
    will satisfy two if it can, or only one if not even two constraints can=
 be
    satisfied together. Note that if not all three can be satisfied
    simultaneously, it is possible that there is more than one combination =
of
    two constraints that could be satisfied. If so, the <a data-link-type=
=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-u=
ser-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-110">User Age=
nt<!---0.032930%--></a> will
    choose.</p>
