        <section>
          <div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h4 id=3D"methods-6">Methods</h4><a=
 class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#metho=
ds-6" aria-label=3D"Permalink for this Section"></a></div>
          <dl data-link-for=3D"ConstrainablePattern" data-dfn-for=3D"Constr=
ainablePattern" class=3D"methods">
            <dt>getCapabilities</dt>
            <dd>
              <p>The <dfn data-lt=3D"getCapabilities()" data-export=3D"" da=
ta-dfn-type=3D"method" id=3D"dom-constrainablepattern-getcapabilities" data=
-idl=3D"operation" data-title=3D"getCapabilities()" data-dfn-for=3D"Constra=
inablePattern" data-type=3D"Capabilities" data-local-lt=3D"ConstrainablePat=
tern.getCapabilities|ConstrainablePattern.getCapabilities()|getCapabilities=
" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog"><code>getCapabilities()</code></d=
fn>
              method returns the dictionary of the names of the constrainab=
le
              properties that the object supports. When invoked, the <a dat=
a-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-=
main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-11=
8">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a>
              <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> return the v=
alue of the <a data-link-for=3D"constrainable object" data-link-type=3D"att=
ribute" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-capabilities-0=
" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-capabilities-0-5">[[Capabilities]=
]</a> internal
              slot.</p>
              <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-28"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-2=
8" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span><!---0.032930%--></div><div class=3D""=
>
                <p>It is possible that the underlying hardware may not exac=
tly
                map to the range defined for the constrainable property. Wh=
ere
                this is possible, the entry <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD<!-=
--0.032930%--></em> define how to translate and
                scale the hardware's setting onto the values defined for th=
e
                property. For example, suppose that a hypothetical
                fluxCapacitance property ranges from -10 (min) to 10 (max),=
 but
                there are common hardware devices that support only values =
of
                "off" "medium" and "full". The constrainable property
                definition might specify that for such hardware, the <a dat=
a-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-=
main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-11=
9">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a>
                should map the range value of -10 to "off", 10 to "full", a=
nd 0
                to "medium". It might also indicate that given a Constraint=
Set
                imposing a strict value of 3, the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|=
abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agen=
t" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-120">User Agent<!---0=
.032930%--></a> should attempt to
                set the value of "medium" on the hardware, and that
                <!---0.032930%--><a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-xref-type=
=3D"method" data-lt=3D"getSettings()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediaca=
pture-main/#dom-constrainablepattern-getsettings" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dom-constrainablepattern-getsettings-2"><code>getSettings<!---0=
.032930%--></code></a><code>(<!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%--><!---0.03293=
0%-->)</code><!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%--> should return a
                fluxCapacitance of 0, since that is the value defined as
                corresponding to "medium".</p>
              </div></div>
            </dd>
            <dt><a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=
=3D"getConstraints" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-co=
nstrainablepattern-getconstraints" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-=
constrainablepattern-getconstraints-4"><code>getConstraints<!---0.032930%--=
></code></a><!---0.032930%--></dt>
            <dd>
              <p>The <dfn data-export=3D"" data-dfn-type=3D"method" id=3D"d=
om-constrainablepattern-getconstraints" data-idl=3D"operation" data-title=
=3D"getConstraints()" data-dfn-for=3D"ConstrainablePattern" data-type=3D"Co=
nstraints" data-lt=3D"getConstraints()" data-local-lt=3D"ConstrainablePatte=
rn.getConstraints|ConstrainablePattern.getConstraints()|getConstraints" tab=
index=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog"><code>getConstraints()</code></dfn> me=
thod returns the Constraints
              that were the argument to the most recent successful invocati=
on
              of the <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#df=
n-applyconstraints-algorithm" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" =
id=3D"ref-for-dfn-applyconstraints-algorithm-4">ApplyConstraints algorithm<=
/a> on the object,
              maintaining the order in which they were specified. Note that
              some of the advanced ConstraintSets returned may not be curre=
ntly
              satisfied. To check which ConstraintSets are currently in eff=
ect,
              the application should use <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-l=
ink-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"getSettings" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/medi=
acapture-main/#dom-constrainablepattern-getsettings" class=3D"internalDFN" =
id=3D"ref-for-dom-constrainablepattern-getsettings-3"><code>getSettings<!--=
-0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%-->. Instead of
              returning the exact constraints as described above, the UA <e=
m class=3D"rfc2119">MAY<!---0.032930%--></em>
              return a constraint set that has the identical effect in all
              situations as the applied constraints. When invoked, the <a d=
ata-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacaptur=
e-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-=
121">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a>
              <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> return the v=
alue of the <a data-link-for=3D"constrainable object" data-link-type=3D"att=
ribute" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-constraints" c=
lass=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-constraints-5">[[Constraints]]</a> i=
nternal slot.
              </p>
            </dd>
            <dt>getSettings</dt>
            <dd>
              <p>The <dfn data-export=3D"" data-dfn-type=3D"method" id=3D"d=
om-constrainablepattern-getsettings" data-idl=3D"operation" data-title=3D"g=
etSettings()" data-dfn-for=3D"ConstrainablePattern" data-type=3D"Settings" =
data-lt=3D"getSettings()" data-local-lt=3D"ConstrainablePattern.getSettings=
|ConstrainablePattern.getSettings()|getSettings" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspop=
up=3D"dialog"><code>getSettings()</code></dfn> method returns the current
              settings of all the constrainable properties of the object,
              whether they are platform defaults or have been set by the
              <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-apply=
constraints-algorithm" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"r=
ef-for-dfn-applyconstraints-algorithm-5">ApplyConstraints algorithm</a>. No=
te that a setting is a
              target value that complies with constraints, and therefore ma=
y
              differ from measured performance at times. When invoked, the =
User
              Agent <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> return=
 the value of the <a data-link-for=3D"constrainable object" data-link-type=
=3D"attribute" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-setting=
s-0" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-settings-0-5">[[Settings]]</a>
              internal slot.</p>
            </dd>
            <dt>applyConstraints</dt>
            <dd>
              <p>When the <dfn id=3D"dfn-applyconstraints-template-method" =
tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">applyConstrai=
nts template method</dfn> is invoked, the
              <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.git=
hub.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-f=
or-dfn-user-agent-122">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> <em class=3D"rfc2119=
">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> run the following steps:</p>
              <ol class=3D"algorithm">
                <li>
                  <p>Let <var>object</var> be the object on which this meth=
od
                  was invoked.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>Let <var>newConstraints</var> be the argument to this
                  method.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>Let <var>p</var> be a new promise.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>Run the following steps in parallel, maintaining the o=
rder
                  of invocations if this method is called multiple times:</=
p>
                  <ol>
                    <li>
                      <p>Let <var>failedConstraint</var> be the result of
                      running the <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacap=
ture-main/#dfn-applyconstraints-algorithm" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-=
type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-applyconstraints-algorithm-6">ApplyConstrain=
ts algorithm</a> with
                      <var>newConstraints</var> as the argument.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <p>Let <var>successfulSettings</var> be the
                      <var>object</var>'s current settings after the algori=
thm
                      in the above step has finished.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <p>Queue a task that runs the following steps:</p>
                      <ol>
                        <li>
                          <p>If <var>failedConstraint</var> is not
                          <code>undefined</code>, let <var>message</var> be=
 either
                          <code>undefined</code> or an informative human-re=
adable
                          message, <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" data-cite=3D"w=
ebidl" data-cite-path=3D"" data-cite-frag=3D"reject" href=3D"https://webidl=
.spec.whatwg.org/#reject">reject<!---0.032930%--></a> <var>p</var> with a n=
ew
                          <code>OverconstrainedError</code> created by call=
ing
                          <code>OverconstrainedError(<var>failedConstraint<=
/var>,
                          <var>message</var>)</code>, and abort these steps=
. The
                          existing constraints remain in effect in this cas=
e.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <p>Set <var>object</var>'s <a data-link-for=3D"co=
nstrainable object" data-link-type=3D"attribute" href=3D"https://w3c.github=
.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-constraints" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for=
-dfn-constraints-6">[[Constraints]]</a>
                          internal slot to <var>newConstraints</var> or a
                          <code>Constraints</code> dictionary that has the
                          identical effect in all situations as
                          <var>newConstraints</var>.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <p>Set <var>object</var>'s <a data-link-for=3D"co=
nstrainable object" data-link-type=3D"attribute" href=3D"https://w3c.github=
.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-settings-0" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-=
dfn-settings-0-6">[[Settings]]</a>
                          internal slot to <var>successfulSettings</var>.</=
p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <p><a data-link-type=3D"dfn" data-cite=3D"webidl"=
 data-cite-path=3D"" data-cite-frag=3D"resolve" href=3D"https://webidl.spec=
.whatwg.org/#resolve">resolve<!---0.032930%--></a> <var>p</var> with
                          <code>undefined</code>.</p>
                        </li>
                      </ol>
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>Return <var>p</var>.</p>
                </li>
              </ol>
              <p>The <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://=
w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-applyconstraints-algorithm" class=3D"i=
nternalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-applyconstraints-algorithm-7">ApplyConstraint=
s algorithm<!---0.032930%--></a> for applying constraints
              is stated below. Here are some preliminary definitions that a=
re
              used in the statement of the algorithm:</p>
              <p>We use the term <dfn data-export=3D"" data-plurals=3D"sett=
ings dictionaries" id=3D"dfn-settings-dictionary" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspo=
pup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">settings dictionary</dfn> for the set =
of
              values that might be applied as settings to the object.</p>
              <p>For string valued constraints, we define "=3D=3D" below to=
 be true
              if one of the values in the sequence is exactly the same as t=
he
              value being compared against.</p>
              <p>We define the <dfn data-export=3D"" id=3D"dfn-fitness-dist=
ance" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">fitness=
 distance</dfn> between a
              <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-setti=
ngs-dictionary" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-=
dfn-settings-dictionary-5">settings dictionary</a> and a constraint set <va=
r>CS</var> as
              the sum, for each member (represented by a
              <var>constraintName</var> and <var>constraintValue</var> pair=
)
              which <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" data-link-for=3D"map" data-xr=
ef-for=3D"map" data-cite=3D"infra" data-cite-path=3D"" data-cite-frag=3D"ma=
p-exists" href=3D"https://infra.spec.whatwg.org/#map-exists">exist<!---0.03=
2930%--></a>s in
              <var>CS</var>, of the following values:</p>
              <ol>
                <li>
                  <p>If <var>constraintName</var> is not supported by the
                  <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c=
.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"r=
ef-for-dfn-user-agent-123">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a>, the fitness dis=
tance is 0.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>If the constraint is <dfn id=3D"dfn-required" tabindex=
=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">required</dfn>
                  (<var>constraintValue</var>
                  either contains one or more members named 'min', 'max', o=
r
                  'exact', or is itself a bare value in an advanced
                  ConstraintSet), and the <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/=
mediacapture-main/#dfn-settings-dictionary" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link=
-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-settings-dictionary-6">settings dictionary<=
/a>'s
                  <var>constraintName</var> member's value does not satisfy=
 the
                  constraint or doesn't <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" data-link=
-for=3D"map" data-xref-for=3D"map" data-cite=3D"infra" data-cite-path=3D"" =
data-cite-frag=3D"map-exists" href=3D"https://infra.spec.whatwg.org/#map-ex=
ists">exist<!---0.032930%--></a>, the fitness distance is
                  positive infinity.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>If the constraint does not apply for this type of obje=
ct,
                  the fitness distance is 0 (that is, the constraint does n=
ot
                  influence the fitness distance).</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>If <var>constraintValue</var> is a boolean, but the
                  constrainable property is not, then the fitness distance =
is
                  based on whether the <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/med=
iacapture-main/#dfn-settings-dictionary" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-ty=
pe=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-settings-dictionary-7">settings dictionary</a>=
's
                  <var>constraintName</var> member <a data-link-type=3D"dfn=
" data-link-for=3D"map" data-xref-for=3D"map" data-lt=3D"exist" data-cite=
=3D"infra" data-cite-path=3D"" data-cite-frag=3D"map-exists" href=3D"https:=
//infra.spec.whatwg.org/#map-exists">exists<!---0.032930%--></a> or
                  not, from the formula
                  </p><pre aria-busy=3D"false"><code class=3D"hljs yaml"><s=
pan class=3D"hljs-string">(constraintValue</span> <span class=3D"hljs-strin=
g">=3D=3D</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">exists)</span> <span class=3D"=
hljs-string">?</span> <span class=3D"hljs-attr">0 :</span> <span class=3D"h=
ljs-number">1</span></code></pre>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>If the <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-m=
ain/#dfn-settings-dictionary" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" =
id=3D"ref-for-dfn-settings-dictionary-8">settings dictionary</a>'s <var>con=
straintName</var>
                  member does <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" data-link-for=3D"ma=
p" data-xref-for=3D"map" data-lt=3D"exist" data-cite=3D"infra" data-cite-pa=
th=3D"" data-cite-frag=3D"map-exists" href=3D"https://infra.spec.whatwg.org=
/#map-exists">not exist<!---0.032930%--></a>, the fitness distance
                  is 1.</p>
                </li>
                <li>If no ideal value is specified (<var>constraintValue</v=
ar>
                either contains no member named 'ideal', or, if bare values=
 are
                to be treated as 'ideal', isn't a bare value), the fitness
                distance is 0.</li>
                <li>For all positive numeric constraints (such as
                height, width, frameRate, aspectRatio, sampleRate and
                sampleSize), the fitness distance is the result of the form=
ula
                  <pre aria-busy=3D"false"><code class=3D"hljs yaml"><span =
class=3D"hljs-string">(actual</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">=3D=3D</sp=
an> <span class=3D"hljs-string">ideal)</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">?=
</span> <span class=3D"hljs-attr">0 :</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">|a=
ctual</span> <span class=3D"hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class=3D"hljs-strin=
g">ideal|</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">/</span> <span class=3D"hljs-s=
tring">max(|actual|,</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">|ideal|)</span></co=
de></pre>
                </li>
                <li>For all string, enum and boolean constraints (e.g.
                deviceId, groupId, facingMode, resizeMode, echoCancellation=
),
                the fitness distance is the result of the formula
                  <pre aria-busy=3D"false"><code class=3D"hljs yaml"><span =
class=3D"hljs-string">(actual</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">=3D=3D</sp=
an> <span class=3D"hljs-string">ideal)</span> <span class=3D"hljs-string">?=
</span> <span class=3D"hljs-attr">0 :</span> <span class=3D"hljs-number">1<=
/span></code></pre>
                </li>
              </ol>
              <p>More definitions:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>We refer to each element of a ConstraintSet (other than=
 the
                special term 'advanced') as a 'constraint' since it is inte=
nded
                to constrain the acceptable settings for the given property
                from the full list or range given in the corresponding
                Capability of the ConstrainablePattern object to a value th=
at
                is within the range or list of values it specifies.</li>
                <li>We refer to the "effective Capability" C of an object O=
 as
                the possibly proper subset of the possible values of C (as
                returned by getCapabilities) taking into consideration
                environmental limitations and/or restrictions placed by oth=
er
                constraints. For example given a ConstraintSet that constra=
ins
                the aspectRatio, height, and width properties, the values
                assigned to any two of the properties limit the effective
                Capability of the third. The set of effective Capabilities =
may
                be platform dependent. For example, on a resource-limited
                device it may not be possible to set properties P1 and P2 b=
oth
                to 'high', while on another less limited device, this may b=
e
                possible.</li>
                <li>A settings dictionary, which is a set of values for the
                constrainable properties of an object O, satisfies
                ConstraintSet CS if the <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/me=
diacapture-main/#dfn-fitness-distance" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=
=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-fitness-distance-2">fitness distance</a> between=
 the set
                and CS is less than infinity.
                </li>
                <li>A set of ConstraintSets CS1...CSn (n &gt;=3D 1) can be
                satisfied by an object O if it is possible to find a settin=
gs
                dictionary of O that satisfies CS1...CSn simultaneously.</l=
i>
                <li>To apply a set of ConstraintSets CS1...CSn to object O =
is
                to choose such a sequence of values that satisfy CS1...CSn =
and
                assign them as the settings for the properties of O.</li>
              </ul>
              <p>We define the <dfn class=3D"abstract-op" data-dfn-type=3D"=
abstract-op" id=3D"dfn-selectsettings" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dial=
og" data-export=3D"">SelectSettings</dfn> algorithm as
              follows:</p>
              <ol class=3D"algorithm">
                <li>Each <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main=
/#dfn-constraint" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-fo=
r-dfn-constraint-1">constraint</a> specifies one
                or more values (or a range of values) for its property. A
                property <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY<!---0.032930%--></em> ap=
pear more than once in the list of 'advanced'
                ConstraintSets. If an empty list has been given as the valu=
e
                for a constraint, it <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.03293=
0%--></em> be interpreted as if the constraint
                were not specified (in other words, an empty constraint =3D=
=3D no
                constraint).
                  <p>Note that unknown properties are discarded by WebIDL,
                  which means that unknown/unsupported required constraints
                  will silently disappear. To avoid this being a surprise,
                  application authors are expected to first use the
                  <!---0.032930%--><a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-xref-type=
=3D"method" data-link-for=3D"MediaDevices" data-xref-for=3D"MediaDevices" d=
ata-lt=3D"getSupportedConstraints()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacap=
ture-main/#dom-mediadevices-getsupportedconstraints" class=3D"internalDFN" =
id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediadevices-getsupportedconstraints-3"><code>getSupporte=
dConstraints<!---0.032930%--></code></a><code>(<!---0.032930%--><!---0.0329=
30%--><!---0.032930%-->)</code><!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%--> method as=
 shown in the
                  Examples below.</p>
                </li>
                <li>Let <var>object</var> be the
                <code><a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#d=
om-constrainablepattern" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"idl" id=3D=
"ref-for-dom-constrainablepattern-10"><code>ConstrainablePattern</code></a>=
</code> object on which this
                algorithm is applied. Let <var>copy</var> be an unconstrain=
ed
                copy of <var>object</var> (i.e., <var>copy</var> should beh=
ave
                as if it were <var>object</var> with all ConstraintSets
                removed.)</li>
                <li>
                  <p>For every possible <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/me=
diacapture-main/#dfn-settings-dictionary" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-t=
ype=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-settings-dictionary-9">settings dictionary</a=
> of
                  <var>copy</var> compute its <a href=3D"https://w3c.github=
.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-fitness-distance" class=3D"internalDFN" data-lin=
k-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-fitness-distance-3">fitness distance</a>, =
treating
                  bare values of properties as ideal values. Let
                  <var>candidates</var> be the set of <a data-lt=3D"setting=
s dictionary" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-settings=
-dictionary" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn=
-settings-dictionary-10">settings dictionaries</a> for which the
                  fitness distance is finite.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>If <var>candidates</var> is empty, return
                  <code>undefined</code> as the result of the
                  <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-s=
electsettings" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-d=
fn-selectsettings-5">SelectSettings</a> algorithm.</p>
                </li>
                <li>Iterate over the 'advanced' ConstraintSets in
                <var>newConstraints</var> in the order in which they were
                specified. For each ConstraintSet:
                  <ol>
                    <li>
                      <p>compute the <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media=
capture-main/#dfn-fitness-distance" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D=
"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-fitness-distance-4">fitness distance</a> between it=
 and
                      each settings dictionary in <var>candidates</var>,
                      treating bare values of properties as exact.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <p>If the fitness distance is finite for one or more
                      settings dictionaries in <var>candidates</var>, keep
                      those settings dictionaries in <var>candidates</var>,
                      discarding others.</p>
                      <p>If the fitness distance is infinite for all settin=
gs
                      dictionaries in <var>candidates</var>, ignore this
                      ConstraintSet.</p>
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>Select one settings dictionary from <var>candidates</v=
ar>,
                  and return it as the result of the <a href=3D"https://w3c=
.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-selectsettings" class=3D"internalDFN" dat=
a-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-selectsettings-6">SelectSettings</a>
                  algorithm. The <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"inter=
nalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-124">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> <=
em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> use one with the smallest
                  <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-f=
itness-distance" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for=
-dfn-fitness-distance-5">fitness distance</a>, as calculated in step 3. If =
more than
                  one settings dictionary have the smallest fitness distanc=
e,
                  the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https:/=
/w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-125">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> chooses one=
 of them based on system default property values
                  and <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https:/=
/w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-126">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> default pro=
perty values.</p>
                </li>
              </ol>
              <p>For any property with a system default value for the selec=
ted device, the system default value <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD<!---0.032=
930%--></em>
                be used if compatible with the above algorithm. This is usu=
ally the case for properties
                like <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#de=
f-constraint-sampleRate">sampleRate</a> or <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/mediacapture-main/#def-constraint-sampleSize">sampleSize</a>.
                Other properties, like <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/med=
iacapture-main/#def-constraint-echoCancellation">echoCancellation</a> or
                <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#def-con=
straint-resizeMode">resizeMode</a> do not usually have system default value=
s.
                The <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w=
3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D=
"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-127">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> defines its ow=
n default values for these properties.
                Implementors need to be cautious to select good default val=
ues since they will often have
                an impact on how media content is generated.</p>
              <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-29"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-2=
9" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span><!---0.032930%--></div><div class=3D""=
>
                <p>It is recommended to look at existing implementations to=
 select meaningful default values.
                Note that default values may differ based on the system, fo=
r instance desktop vs. mobile.
                At time of writing, <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" h=
ref=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"in=
ternalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-128">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a=
> implementations tend to use the following default values,
                which were chosen for their suitability for using RTCPeerCo=
nnection as a sink:</p>
                <ol>
                  <li><p><a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main=
/#def-constraint-width">width</a> set to 640.</p></li>
                  <li><p><a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main=
/#def-constraint-height">height</a> set to 480.</p></li>
		  <li><p><a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#def-constrai=
nt-frameRate">frameRate</a> set to 30.</p></li>
                  <li><p><a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main=
/#def-constraint-echoCancellation">echoCancellation</a> set to <code>true</=
code>.</p></li>
                </ol>
              </div></div>
              <p>To apply the <dfn class=3D"abstract-op" data-dfn-type=3D"a=
bstract-op" id=3D"dfn-applyconstraints-algorithm" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspo=
pup=3D"dialog" data-export=3D"">ApplyConstraints algorithm</dfn> to an
              <var>object</var>, given <var>newConstraints</var> as an
              argument, the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"h=
ttps://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDF=
N" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-129">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> <em cl=
ass=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> run the following steps:</p>
              <ol class=3D"algorithm">
                <li>
                  <p>Let <var>successfulSettings</var> be the result of run=
ning
                  the <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#d=
fn-selectsettings" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-f=
or-dfn-selectsettings-7">SelectSettings</a> algorithm with
                  <var>newConstraints</var> as the constraint set.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>If <var>successfulSettings</var> is
                  <code>undefined</code>, let <var>failedConstraint</var> b=
e
                  any <a data-lt=3D"required constraints" href=3D"https://w=
3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-required-constraints" class=3D"internal=
DFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-required-constraints-11">requ=
ired constraint</a>
                  whose fitness distance was infinity
                  for all settings dictionaries examined while executing th=
e
                  <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-s=
electsettings" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-d=
fn-selectsettings-8">SelectSettings</a> algorithm, or <code>""</code> if th=
ere
                  isn't one, and then return
                  <var>failedConstraint</var> and abort these steps.</p>
                </li>
                <li>In a single operation, remove the existing constraints =
from
                <var>object</var>, apply <var>newConstraints</var>, and app=
ly
                <var>successfulSettings</var> as the current settings.</li>
                <li>Return <code>undefined</code>.</li>
              </ol>
              <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-30"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-3=
0" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span><!---0.032930%--></div><div class=3D""=
>
                <p>If the UA <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-lt=
=3D"relinquish the device" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/=
#dfn-relinquish-the-device" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-relinqu=
ish-the-device-1">relinquished the device<!---0.032930%--></a>,
                for instance if the track is <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstr=
act-op" data-link-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrac=
k" data-lt=3D"muted" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#track=
-muted" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-muted-15">muted<!---0.032=
930%--></a>,
                applying the settings does not mean changing the device con=
figuration.
                Instead, the UA will configure the device to match the
                track settings at the time the UA is reacquiring the
                device, for instance when the track gets
                <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-link-for=3D"Medi=
aStreamTrack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-lt=3D"muted" href=3D"=
https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#track-muted" class=3D"internalDFN"=
 id=3D"ref-for-track-muted-16">unmuted<!---0.032930%--></a>.</p>
              </div></div>
              <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-31"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-3=
1" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span><!---0.032930%--></div><div class=3D""=
>
                <p>Any implementation that has the same result as the algor=
ithm
                above is an allowed implementation. For instance, the
                implementation may choose to keep track of the maximum and
                minimum values for a setting that are OK under the constrai=
nts
                considered, rather than keeping track of all possible value=
s
                for the setting.</p>
              </div></div>
              <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-32"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-3=
2" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span><!---0.032930%--></div><div class=3D""=
>
                <p>When picking a settings dictionary, the UA can use any
                information available to it. Examples of such information m=
ay
                be whether the selection is done as part of device selectio=
n in
                getUserMedia, whether the energy usage of the camera varies
                between the settings dictionaries, or whether using a setti=
ngs
                dictionary will cause the device driver to apply
                resampling.</p>
              </div></div>
              <p>The <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://=
w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-130">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> <em class=
=3D"rfc2119">MAY<!---0.032930%--></em> choose new settings for the constrai=
nable
              properties of the object at any time. When it does so it <em =
class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em>
              attempt to satisfy all current Constraints, in the manner
              described in the algorithm above, let
              <var>successfulSettings</var> be the resulting new settings, =
and
              queue a task to run the following steps:</p>
              <ol class=3D"algorithm">
                <li>
                  <p>Let <var>object</var> be the
                  <code><a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/=
#dom-constrainablepattern" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"idl" id=
=3D"ref-for-dom-constrainablepattern-11"><code>ConstrainablePattern</code><=
/a></code> object on which new
                  settings for one or more constrainable properties have ch=
anged.
                  </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>Set <var>object</var>'s <a data-link-for=3D"constraina=
ble object" data-link-type=3D"attribute" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/medi=
acapture-main/#dfn-settings-0" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-sett=
ings-0-7">[[Settings]]</a> internal
                  slot to <var>successfulSettings</var>.</p>
                </li>
              </ol>
            </dd>
          </dl>
        </section>
      </div>
      <p>An example of Constraints that could be passed into
      <!---0.032930%--><a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-xref-type=3D"method" =
data-link-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-xref-for=3D"MediaStreamTrack" data-=
lt=3D"applyConstraints()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#=
dom-mediastreamtrack-applyconstraints" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-=
dom-mediastreamtrack-applyconstraints-7"><code>applyConstraints<!---0.03293=
0%--></code></a><code>(<!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%-->)=
</code><!---0.032930%--><!---0.032930%-->
      or returned as a value of <code><a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/medi=
acapture-main/#dom-constraints" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"idl=
" id=3D"ref-for-dom-constraints-8">constraints</a></code> is below. It
      uses the <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#constrai=
nable-properties">constrainable properties</a>
      defined for camera-sourced <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=
=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaStreamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediaca=
pture-main/#dom-mediastreamtrack" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-m=
ediastreamtrack-123"><code>MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!--=
-0.032930%-->s. In this example, all
      constraints are ideal values, which means results are "best effort" b=
ased
      on the user's specific camera:</p>
      <div class=3D"example" id=3D"example-4">
        <div class=3D"marker">
    <a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/=
#example-4">Example<!---0.032930%--><bdi> 4<!---0.032930%--></bdi></a><!---=
0.032930%-->
  </div><!---0.032930%--> <pre aria-busy=3D"false"><code class=3D"hljs java=
script"><span class=3D"hljs-keyword">await</span> track.<span class=3D"hljs=
-title function_">applyConstraints</span>({
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">width</span>: <span class=3D"hljs-number">1920<=
/span>,
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">height</span>: <span class=3D"hljs-number">1080=
</span>,
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">frameRate</span>: <span class=3D"hljs-number">3=
0</span>,
});
<span class=3D"hljs-keyword">const</span> {width, height, frameRate} =3D tr=
