    <section id=3D"capabilities"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h3 id=3D"x1=
1-3-capabilities"><bdi class=3D"secno">11.3<!---0.032930%--> </bdi>Capabili=
ties</h3><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-=
main/#capabilities" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 11.3"></a></div>
     =20
      <p><dfn data-dfn-type=3D"dictionary" data-export=3D"" id=3D"dom-capab=
ilities" data-idl=3D"dictionary" data-title=3D"Capabilities" data-dfn-for=
=3D"" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog"><code>Capabilities</code></df=
n> is a dictionary containing one or more
      key-value pairs, where each key <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.0329=
30%--></em> be a constrainable property, and
      each value <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> be a subs=
et of the set of values allowed for that
      property. The exact syntax of the value expression depends on the typ=
e of
      the property. The Capabilities dictionary specifies which constrainab=
le
      properties that can be applied, as constraints, to the <a href=3D"htt=
ps://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-constrainable-object" class=3D"in=
ternalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-constrainable-object-4"=
>constrainable
      object</a>. Note that the Capabilities of a <a href=3D"https://w3c.gi=
thub.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-constrainable-object" class=3D"internalDFN" =
data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-constrainable-object-5">constraina=
ble object</a>
      <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY<!---0.032930%--></em> be a subset of the pr=
operties defined in the Web platform, with a
      subset of the set values for those properties. Note that Capabilities=
 are
      returned from the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https=
://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" i=
d=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-133">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> to the app=
lication, and cannot be specified
      by the application. However, the application can control the Settings
      that the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.gi=
thub.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-=
for-dfn-user-agent-134">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> chooses for constra=
inable properties by means of
      Constraints.</p>
      <p>An example of a Capabilities dictionary is shown below. In this ca=
se,
      the <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-constrain=
able-object" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn=
-constrainable-object-6">constrainable object</a> is a video source with a =
very limited set
      of Capabilities.</p>
      <div class=3D"example" id=3D"example-11">
        <div class=3D"marker">
    <a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/=
#example-11">Example<!---0.032930%--><bdi> 11<!---0.032930%--></bdi></a><!-=
--0.032930%-->
  </div><!---0.032930%--> <pre aria-busy=3D"false"><code class=3D"hljs css"=
>{
  frameRate: {min: <span class=3D"hljs-number">1.0</span>, max: <span class=
=3D"hljs-number">60.0</span>},
  facingMode: [<span class=3D"hljs-string">'user'</span>, <span class=3D"hl=
js-string">'left'</span>]
}</code></pre><!---0.032930%-->
      </div>
      <p>The next example below points out that capabilities for range valu=
es
      provide ranges for individual constrainable properties, not combinati=
ons.
      This is particularly relevant for video width and height, since the
      ranges for width and height are reported separately. In the example, =
if
      the <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-constrain=
able-object" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"dfn" id=3D"ref-for-dfn=
-constrainable-object-7">constrainable object</a> can only provide 640x480 =
and 800x600
      resolutions the relevant capabilities returned would be:</p>
      <div class=3D"example" id=3D"example-12">
        <div class=3D"marker">
    <a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/=
#example-12">Example<!---0.032930%--><bdi> 12<!---0.032930%--></bdi></a><!-=
--0.032930%-->
  </div><!---0.032930%--> <pre aria-busy=3D"false"><code class=3D"hljs yaml=
">{
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">width:</span> {<span class=3D"hljs-attr">min:</=
span> <span class=3D"hljs-number">640</span>, <span class=3D"hljs-attr">max=
:</span> <span class=3D"hljs-number">800</span>},
  <span class=3D"hljs-attr">height:</span> {<span class=3D"hljs-attr">min:<=
/span> <span class=3D"hljs-number">480</span>, <span class=3D"hljs-attr">ma=
