gs" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 11.4"></a></div>
     =20
      <p><dfn data-export=3D"" data-dfn-type=3D"dictionary" id=3D"dom-setti=
ngs" data-idl=3D"dictionary" data-title=3D"Settings" data-dfn-for=3D"" tabi=
ndex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog"><code>Settings</code></dfn> is a dictio=
nary containing one or more key-value
      pairs. It <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> contain ea=
ch key returned in
      <code>getCapabilities()</code> for which the property is defined on t=
he
      object type it's returned on; for instance, an audio
      <a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSt=
reamTrack" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-mediastream=
track" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediastreamtrack-124"><code>=
MediaStreamTrack<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%--> has no "width=
" property. There <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em>
      be a single value for each key and the value <em class=3D"rfc2119">MU=
ST<!---0.032930%--></em> be a member of the set
      defined for that property by <code>getCapabilities()</code>. The
      <code>Settings</code> dictionary contains the actual values that the =
User
      Agent has chosen for the object's constrainable properties. The exact
      syntax of the value depends on the type of the property.</p>
      <p>A conforming <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https:/=
/w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-135">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> <em class=
=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> support all the constrainable prope=
rties
      defined in this specification.</p>
      <p>An example of a Settings dictionary is shown below. This example i=
s
      not very realistic in that a <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" hr=
ef=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" class=3D"int=
ernalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-136">User Agent<!---0.032930%--></a>=
 would actually be required to
      support more constrainable properties than just these.</p>
      <div class=3D"example" id=3D"example-13">
