 data-link-type=3D"dict-member" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-=
main/#dom-constraints-advanced" id=3D"ref-for-dom-constraints-advanced-3"><=
code>advanced<!---0.032930%--></code></a>;<!---0.032930%--></span>
};<!---0.032930%--></span><!---0.032930%--></code></pre>
      </div>
        <section id=3D"dictionary-constraints-members"><div class=3D"header=
-wrapper"><h4 id=3D"x11-5-1-dictionary-constraints-members"><bdi class=3D"s=
ecno">11.5.1<!---0.032930%--> </bdi>Dictionary <dfn data-export=3D"" data-d=
fn-type=3D"dictionary" id=3D"dom-constraints" data-idl=3D"dictionary" data-=
title=3D"Constraints" data-dfn-for=3D"" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dia=
log"><code>Constraints</code></dfn> Members</h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dictionary-constraints-members=
" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 11.5.1"></a></div>
         =20
          <dl data-link-for=3D"Constraints" data-dfn-for=3D"Constraints" cl=
ass=3D"dictionary-members">
            <dt><dfn data-export=3D"" data-dfn-type=3D"dict-member" id=3D"d=
om-constraints-advanced" data-idl=3D"field" data-title=3D"advanced" data-df=
n-for=3D"Constraints" data-type=3D"sequence" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=
=3D"dialog"><code>advanced</code></dfn> of type <span class=3D"idlMemberTyp=
e">sequence&lt;<a data-xref-type=3D"_IDL_" data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=
=3D"ConstraintSet" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-con=
straintset" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-constraintset-6"><code>=
ConstraintSet<!---0.032930%--></code></a><!---0.032930%-->&gt;</span></dt>
            <dd>
              <p>This is the list of ConstraintSets that the <a data-link-t=
ype=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#df=
n-user-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-138">User =
Agent<!---0.032930%--></a> <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em>
              attempt to satisfy, in order, skipping only those that cannot=
 be
              satisfied. The order of these ConstraintSets is significant. =
In
              particular, when they are passed as an argument to
              <code>applyConstraints</code>, the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|a=
bstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent=
" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-139">User Agent<!---0.=
032930%--></a> <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> try to sati=
sfy
              them in the order that is specified. Thus if advanced
              ConstraintSets C1 and C2 can be satisfied individually, but n=
ot
              together, then whichever of C1 and C2 is first in this list w=
ill
              be satisfied, and the other will not. The <a data-link-type=
=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-u=
ser-agent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-140">User Age=
nt<!---0.032930%--></a> <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST<!---0.032930%--></em> at=
tempt
              to satisfy all ConstraintSets in the list, even if some canno=
t be
              satisfied. Thus, in the preceding example, if constraint C3 i=
s
              specified after C1 and C2, the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstr=
act-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dfn-user-agent" cl=
ass=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-user-agent-141">User Agent<!---0.0329=
30%--></a> will attempt to satisfy
              C3 even though C2 cannot be satisfied. Note that a given prop=
erty
              name may occur only once in each ConstraintSet but may occur =
in
              more than one ConstraintSet.</p>
            </dd>
          </dl>
        </section>
